title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool and frost with pumpkin cake frosting.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add egg yolks.
Add baking soda to sour cream.
Add flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gently fold in egg whites, vanilla and lemon extract last. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: mrs. mclamb's sour cream enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas in hot water for a few seconds, then put meat in tortilla.
Roll and stack side by side in a 9 x 13-inch pan, with crease down.
Pour sour cream and soup mixture over enchiladas; top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water, oatmeal and margarine together. Let stand until margarine melts.
Add brown sugar, white sugar and eggs. Sift soda, cinnamon, salt and flour together.
Add to mixture and bake 35 minutes at 350° in 8 x 12-inch loaf pan.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package instructions.
Cook broccoli according to package instructions.
Combine all ingredients in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Stir well until cheese is nearly melted.
Cover casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk honey rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat buttermilk
to lukewarm.
Pour 1/3 cup of it into medium size bowl and sprinkle in yeast.
Let stand until yeast is dissolved and starts to swell.

title: spinach lazagne
directions: Thaw and drain spinach, then mix with Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella, egg and seasonings.
Spread 1/2 cup of spaghetti sauce in bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan.
Place one-third of uncooked lasagne noodles on sauce, then spread with half of spinach mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles, sauce and 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Pour water around edges.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate lovers bread
directions: Mix all together.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.

title: mocha truffles
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Add cream cheese, coffee and water. Mix well.
Chill until firm enough to shape.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on a wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours until firm.
Melt chocolate coating.
Dip balls and place on wax paper to harden.
If desired, melt white coating and drizzle over truffles. Yields about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: finger paint
directions: To 1 quart of boiling water, add all the other ingredients. Stir until well mixed.
Pour into jars and color with poster paint or vegetable coloring.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt, baking powder and cocoa with flour.
Add milk and vanilla. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: shrimp stir-fry(serves 4)
directions: In nonstick 12-inch skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil and cook cleaned shrimp until lightly brown.
Add garlic and cook 1 minute. Remove to bowl and set aside.
In same pan, cook mushrooms and snap peas until heated through.
In cup, mix teriyaki, cornstarch, ground ginger and 1/2 cup wine.
Add to mushrooms and peas.
Add shrimp and heat through.
Serve over rice.
Prep time:
30 minutes.

title: baked key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine the sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks in bowl, mixing well.
Add lime juice a little at a time, stirring well after each addition to mix and blend well. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into milk mixture carefully until no egg white shows.
Pour carefully into pie shell spreading evenly; will be very full.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Can be served plain or with whipped cream.
This method takes care of the danger of raw eggs.
Baking at 300° will kill any bacteria.

title: rice dish
directions: Mix rice, water, soup, onion mix, salt and pepper to taste. Place chicken or pork chops on mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 10 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients well and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pistachio instant pudding and crushed pineapple with juice.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend together flour and salt.
Stir in.
Roll dough into balls (1 teaspoon per ball).
Beat egg white slightly with fork.
Dip balls into egg white.
Roll in nuts.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Press thumb gently in center of each.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Fill thumbprints with tinted icing.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: pavlova(a favorite dessert from new zealand)
directions: Beat egg whites with a pinch of salt for 5 to 6 minutes. Gradually add sugar, vinegar and vanilla; beat until real stiff. Fold in lightly 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Using a large plate (ovenware) or large-size pie pan, wet the plate with cold water. Heap the mixture onto the damp surface.
Preheat oven to 400°, then set at 250° and bake for 1 1/2 hours, no longer.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Fill a 9-inch prepared pie shell with apples; pour mixture over apples, dotting with butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: dutchess green bananas
directions: Boil bananas. Mash bananas and rub mashed bananas through sieve.
Add all ingredients except butter and blend.
Make puffs on baking tray, forcing through bag.
Brush with egg white.
Bake until brown.
Serve hot.

title: honey dijon turkey spread
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients until well mixed. Cover and refrigerator.
Yields 2 cups.

title: honey mustard mayonnaise
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Great as a spread for turkey sandwiches, chicken salad or as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: hearty lasagna soup
directions: Cook beef with garlic in skillet until browned.
Pour off fat. Add broth, tomatoes and Italian seasoning.
Heat to a boil.
Stir in pasta.
Cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until pasta is done. Sir in cheese.
Serve with additional cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: soy pork or chicken marinade
directions: Mix together all ingredients except meat.
Marinate meat in mixture for 2 to 4 hours or overnight.
Grill meat.

title: crock-pot continental chicken
directions: Arrange dried beef on bottom of greased crock-pot.
Wrap each piece of boned chicken with strip of bacon and place on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together; pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours (high 3 to 4 hours).
Serve over hot buttered noodles or rice.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Toast 1/2 cup coconut and set aside. Bake pastry shell for 8 minutes; cool slightly.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add Eagle Brand milk, water, vanilla, salt and nutmeg; mix well.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup coconut. Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut. Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool and chill, if desired.

title: coffee chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with oil, vinegar, vanilla and cold water. Add coffee last and mix well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: old world salad
directions: Combine lettuce, tomato and onion.
Add olives, salt and pepper; toss.
Add olive oil and vinegar; toss.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine together; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, margarine and powdered sugar together; beat for 15 minutes, until fluffy.
Spread over unbaked graham cracker crust.
Cut into individual servings and put in sauce dish.
Add on top the bananas and pineapple, then top with whipped topping, completely covering all fruit.
Garnish with cherries and chopped nuts and drizzle chocolate syrup over the top of dish.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini (do not peel); cook in small amount of water until just crispy tender.
Drain.
Cook beef in skillet until lightly browned; add onion, cover and cook over low heat until onion is tender.
Season to taste.

title: heavenly banana delight
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix instant pudding, condensed milk and sweet milk together for 2 to 3 minutes.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Whip the whipping cream.
Add whipped cream and sour cream to the chilled pudding mixture.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix well and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and cover with damp paper towel 2 to 3 hours for flavors to blend.
Cut into serving pieces and serve with salsa.

title: "dr.  bird cake"
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add undrained pineapple, oil, vanilla, eggs and bananas, mixing until blended.
Do not beat. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.

title: classic banana cream pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in water in heavy saucepan. Stir in milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Slice 2 bananas and dip in lemon juice; drain.
Arrange on bottom of pastry shell.
Pour filling over bananas; cover; chill 4 hours or until set.
Spread top with whipped cream.
Slice remaining banana and dip in lemon juice; drain; garnish top of pie.

title: angel hair pasta with crab
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
In frying pan over medium heat, place margarine and oil.
When margarine is melted, add green onions, garlic and tomatoes.
Cook, stirring until mixture boils.
Adjust heat so mixture boils gently and cook for 2 minutes.
Mix in lemon juice, crab and parsley.
Cook just until crab is heated.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Spoon sauce over pasta.
Lift and mix pasta gently.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Sprinkle rice in melted butter. Lay cut chicken in.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over.
Pour water, then spread cream of mushroom soup over.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Turn off and let set 1 hour.
Serve hot!
Bake at 375°.

title: boiled custard
directions: Separate egg yolks and whites.
Beat whites until light; add to hot milk (not boiling).
Cook until right thickness.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites to custard (after being cooled), then add vanilla and pour into glasses and chill.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Put through grinder with coarse blade and mix well.
A little mayonnaise might be added.

title: bread pudding
directions: Use day old bread, crust and all, cutting it into 1/4 to 1/2-inch cubes.
Place these in a buttered, 1-quart baking dish. Scald milk with butter and sugar.
Beat the eggs slightly; add salt, then stir into the warm milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour over the bread cubes.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Set the baking dish in a pan containing warm water up to the level of the pudding and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until knife comes out clean when inserted in center of pudding.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: country ham and potatoes
directions: In large skillet melt butter. Brown ham on both sides. Move ham to one side of skillet and brown potatoes in drippings.

title: liver in gravy
directions: Fry bacon. Remove from pan and saute onions in fat. Remove onions.
Blanch liver. Coat with flour and fry in bacon fat. Remove and keep warm with onions.
Add water and onion soup to bacon fat.
Add flour to make gravy.
Put liver and onions in bowl and pour gravy over.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, peas, green onions and water chestnuts in a bowl and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard. Spread over top of salad. Seal and cool. Just before serving, add chopped eggs and crumbled bacon to top of salad. Cover with chips of your choice.

title: quick peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk and butter together.
Pour into a long glass dish.
Add peaches on top.
Cook at 400° until crust rises to top and browns.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on the box, adding 3 tablespoons of creme de menthe.
Bake at 350° as suggested on box. Cool cake completely.
Spread fudge topping on top of cooled cake.
Add 1 tablespoon creme de menthe to Cool Whip, then spread on top of fudge topping.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add sauce and heat.
Cook macaroni; pour sauce mixture into macaroni.
Let simmer a bit and serve.

title: ice cream delite
directions: Melt ice cream slightly, cut in squares.
Pour hot Jell-O (mixed with hot water) over ice cream.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate (sets quickly).

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream and refrigerate above for several hours.
Divide dough into 3 sections.
Roll on floured board, cut with cookie round and fill lightly with jam.
Fold in half and close with edge of fork. Bake at 350° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: marion's muffins(yields 12 muffins)
directions: Pour enough boiling water over raisins to cover.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain well.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oat bran, brown sugar, rice bran, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and allspice.
Make a well in the center. In medium mixing bowl, combine mashed banana, milk, egg whites, cooking oil and vanilla.
Add all to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Fold in raisins, carrots and nuts.
Lightly grease muffin cup or line with paper bake cups.
Fill 2/3 full. Bake in 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Wash and cut tomatoes in 1/2-inch slices.
Dredge thickly with flour.
Fry quickly in oil, browning on both sides.
Remove to serving plate and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.

title: fresh mushroom salad
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, combine ingredients. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Arrange leaves from four Belgian endives around large salad bowl.
Place marinated mushrooms in center.

title: oke oyinko(pineapple drink; african)
directions: Put pineapple slices through sieve to extract juice.
Add hot water to pineapple juice and sweeten to taste.
Add lemon or lime juice.
Add cloves and let cool.
Serve chilled.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours (high for 3 hours).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli cuts completely.
Place broccoli in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook chicken in frying pan (approximately 30 to 45 minutes) until done.
Cut up chicken into small cubes.
Place on top of broccoli.
Combine soup and mayonnaise; add mushrooms, cheese and curry and stir together.
Pour mixture over chicken in pan.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: napa cabbage picnic salad serves a bunch!
directions: Slice cabbage and onions into bite size pieces. Drain water chestnuts and add to cabbage mixture. Store in large air tight container...may be made up to 3 days ahead of time.

title: peas with a flair
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery in butter.
Combine all ingredients in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Brown sausage in pan.
Pour off grease and add cheese to sausage until melted.
Pour into bowl. Add Bisquick and stir. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 36 small biscuits

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside. Sift dry ingredients together and add yeast.
Cut in shortening and then add buttermilk.
Turn out dough onto a floured board and knead for 1 or 2 minutes.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thick and cut into biscuits.
Place biscuits on an ungreased baking sheet, let rise 10 to 15 minutes, then brush with butter and bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: easy deer chops
directions: Trim chops.
Combine dressing and 7-Up soda for marinade. Place marinade in flat glass baking dish.
Turn meat in sauce and put in refrigerator for 1 hour, covered.
Turn meat to other side and let sit in refrigerator for another hour.
Place chops, undrained, on grill and cook to medium rare.

title: squash fritters
directions: Cook squash, drain and mash. Combine squash and next 4 ingredients. Pour oil to depth of 2-inches in a heavy saucepan. Heat to 375°. Drop squash mixture by tablespoon into oil. Fry until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towels. Serve immediately.

title: diet potato cake
directions: Boil raisins in water until all water is gone.
Cool.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon-cheese potato slices
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Scrub potatoes.
Cut into 3/8-inch thick slices.
Arrange in single layer on 12-inch microwave-safe dish.
Sprinkle with onions. Cook, covered with vented clear plastic wrap[, on High, 7 to 10 minutes, giving dish a half turn once.
Sprinkle slices with bacon, olives and cheese.
Cook, uncovered, on 50% power 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.

title: macaroni shrimp salad
directions: Stir vinegar, sugar and Catalina dressing into the first 5 ingredients.
Mix all together with Miracle Whip.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: In a skillet, combine bacon and oil.
Cook over low heat until bacon is rendered.
Add garlic and cook until bacon is crisp.
In a serving bowl, beat eggs well.
Cook spaghetti until done; drain well.
Stir large forkful into eggs.
Add remaining spaghetti and toss.
Add the cheese and toss again.
Add the bacon and serve immediately.

title: v.b.s.  peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat first 5 ingredients together until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Mix with peanut butter mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir dry ingredients into wet mixture. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet, flatten with fork.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 25 dozen small cookies.

title: baked pork chops in gravy
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Open soup and place half in casserole dish, add the pork chops and the remaining soup on top of pork chops.
If mushrooms are desired, put on top of soup. Cover chops and bake for one hour at 350°.
Serve gravy over rice or mashed potatoes.
Try corn with this meal, it is great.

title: creme de menthe  squares
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Combine butter, water, and cocoa in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Pour mixture over dry ingredients, stirring until blended. Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Pour batter into a greased and floured 15x10x1 inch jellyroll pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack. Spread with Creme De Menthe frosting, refrigerate until frosting is firm. Cut into 1 inch squares and drizzle with chocolate. Yield: 48 squares.

title: tortilla cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread onto regular size tortilla a thin layer over the whole tortilla.
Roll up lightly into a log. Wrap them (tortilla logs) individually in plastic wrap and chill them overnight (or 24 hours).
Unwrap plastic from rolls; slice into 2-inch (thick) slices.
Serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Add cracker crumbs and set aside until all liquid is absorbed.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese, to cracker crumb mixture, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese while hot.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Combine strawberries, Cool Whip, walnuts and pineapple tidbits.
Stir in cream cheese mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put in freezer until ready to serve. (Can set down in refrigerator about 15 minutes before serving if you wish.)

title: spring garden dip
directions: Blend sour cream, mayo, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in minced vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: quick chili dip
directions: Combine chili and cheese.
Stir over low heat or put in slow cooker until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips. Makes 2 3/4 cups.

title: tortilla crunch chicken fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine soup mix and tortilla chips.
In a large bowl, combine chicken and egg, beaten with water, coating well.
Dip chicken in tortilla mixture, coating well.

title: tomato cake
directions: Cook tomatoes.
Add raisins to hot tomatoes; let cool.
Melt butter.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add tomatoes and raisins to dry mixture.
Add vanilla, eggs, nuts and butter.
Beat well.
Bake for 1 hour in Bundt pan.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown the chops in frying pan with onion, salt and pepper. Place chops in a baking pan.
Cover chops with white soda cracker crumbs.
Put cream of chicken soup in the frying pan which the chops were browned in.
Add 1 can of milk.
Stir until smooth and mixed with the residue from the chops.
Pour milk/soup mixture over the cracker crumbs and chops.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with fried rice with almonds.

title: bibingka("rice" cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and cheese.
Add slightly beaten eggs and milk.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to mixture.
When mixture is well blended, pour in 2 round cake pans (be sure to grease them).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Before cake is done, spread butter/margarine on top of cake and then sprinkle sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Broil for a few minutes until golden brown.
Be careful not to burn.

title: wheat germ buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Beat egg, buttermilk and margarine together and add to dry mixture until batter is smooth. Fry on hot, lightly greased griddle.
Turn when bubbles appear. Serve with honey or maple syrup.
Makes about 20.

title: old fashioned herb meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Lightly pat mixture into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: quick refrigerator sweet pickles(diabetic recipe)
directions: Place sliced cucumbers and garlic in a glass bowl. In a medium saucepan, combine water, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric. Bring to boiling. Add onion and carrots; cook 2 minutes. Add vinegar; bring just to boiling. Remove from heat; stir in Equal. Pour over cucumbers and garlic. Cool. Cover and chill at least 24 hours before serving. Store in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: In small bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl cream butter and sugar.
Mix in the egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, cereal and chips.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake for 12 - 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: betty's cucumber salad
directions: Cook vinegar, water, salt and sugar until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers and chill. Score cucumbers with fork; do not peel.
Cut onions in rings. Add to cucumbers.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes. Remove from oven, spread with marshmallows.
Return to oven and melt for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool cake 20 minutes before icing.

title: chicken almond bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch ovenproof pan.

title: chile  cheese dip
directions: Beat cream cheese with seasoned salt until fluffy.
Gradually beat in mayonnaise.
Drain tomatoes and break up; drain well. Drain chilies; press out liquid.
Stir tomatoes, chilies and onion into cheese mixture.
Cover tightly and chill overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with chips or as a spread.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes two loaves.

title: liver deluxe
directions: Dredge pieces of liver with flour and seasonings.
Brown gently on both sides in butter.
Make sauce by blending together the last four ingredients.
Pour over liver and cook 25 minutes on very low heat.
Place on hot serving platter, top with the sauce and serve.
Serves 4.

title: cream of artichoke soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion, carrots and celery in 1/4 cup butter.
Add bay leaf, thyme, oregano, cayenne, broth, mushrooms and artichokes.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
In small skillet, melt remaining butter over low heat.
Stir in flour and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Stir into artichoke mixture. Slowly add cream, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes until slightly thickened and heated through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade hamburger helper
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Drain.
Add soup and macaroni. Mix.

title: honey-bran muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Combine bran flakes and milk in bowl; mix well.
Let stand for 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in egg, oil and honey; beat well.
Add dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tests done.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk and vegetables.
Cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Serve.

title: vietnam cookies
directions: Blend until creamy shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mash bananas and add alternately with flour mixture to sugar mixture. Add and stir in walnuts, chocolate chips, coconut, raisins and oats.

title: ti-leaf 'aina ahiahi
directions: Line heavy roasting pan with 4 of the deveined and washed ti leaves.
Place thawed but uncooked spinach leaves on ti leaves. Arrange pork and fish on top of spinach after brushing each one with liquid smoke.
Add sliced onions and sprinkle on Hawaiian salt (about 2 teaspoons).

title: fresh pea soup
directions: Place ham in large kettle with water.
Boil until cooked and remove meat (approximately 2 to 4 cups of cubed ham).
Grind in food grinder peas, carrots, onions and potatoes.
Add to stock of ham.
Bring all to a boil and then turn down to simmer for about 2 hours.
Enjoy!
Add ham cubes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together and shape into patties.
Fry until done.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients together; crumble butter or margarine into mixture. Add slightly beaten egg and orange juice.
When mixture is moist, add raisins and cranberries.
Pour in a greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve at Thanksgiving.
Delicious with a pat of butter on it.

title: 5-hour beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cover and bake for 5 hours.
Do NOT peek!!!

title: quick spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches.	Put juice in 2 quart boiler.
Add other ingredients and boil 1 or 2
minutes.
Pour
over
peaches and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight or up to 2 weeks.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Cut 1/4 of one cucumber into thin slices; set aside.
Cut remaining cucumber into bite-size cubes.
Cut pepper into thin julienne strips.
In large bowl combine cucumber cubes, green pepper, corn and onion.
In a small bowl combine oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss to coat well with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly and roll in chopped nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: ann's 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in large casserole or pan as listed, except mayo and cheese.
Combine them and spread over top of salad.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: cream cheese delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine and 1 tablespoon of sugar; reserve 1/2 cup.
Press remainder into bottom and sides of an 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch baking pan or large casserole dish except 1/2 cheese, 1/2 onions and rolls.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Unwrap rolls, separate into rectangles and cut into strips.
Make lattice top.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Add remaining cheese and onions, bake 3 to 5 minutes more and serve.

title: alamo elementary spaghetti(yields 100 one-cup servings)
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, peppers and parsley flakes.
Drain. Add tomato paste.
Add water to own thickness. Boil noodles and margarine.
Combine salt and pepper to taste.
Top with cheese.

title: apricot corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray or coat lightly with vegetable oil.
Finely chop the dried apricots and set aside.
Mix flour with corn meal, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar in a large bowl. In another bowl, combine buttermilk, eggs, oil and honey.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients and mix until just blended. Spoon batter into loaf pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Gently loosen sides of pan. Turn onto wire rack to cool completely.
Makes 1 loaf.
Each slice contains 182 calories and 5 grams fat (26% from fat).

title: 5-minute cake
directions: Put softened butter in a 1-cup measuring cup.
Add the egg, then enough milk to fill cup.
Sift dry ingredients together. Pour liquid into dry ingredients and beat 5 minutes.
Bake at about 375° as muffins, loaf or layers.

title: reuben meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/4 can soup, beef, corned beef, bread crumbs, eggs, parsley and garlic. On waxed paper, pat meat firmly in a rectangle (15 x 10). In bowl, combine sauerkraut, cheese and caraway and press mixture into meat within 1-inch of edges. Roll meat tightly in a jelly roll fashion; seal seams and ends. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: date and nut cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Lightly brown mushrooms and green pepper in butter.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk and seasoning.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir some of hot mixture into beaten egg yolk.
Add other ingredients and cook 10 minutes longer.
Add chicken and pimentos just before serving.
Serve in pastry shells.

title: seven cup salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Cover and put in icebox for several hours or at least one day.
The reason for this is the salad actually improves in taste after it sets in icebox.

title: crab dip
directions: In a fairly
large
pot,
place
gelatin
and hot water (over medium heat) and
add
soup.
Do not overcook, just heat until mixture reaches
boiling,
but do not boil.
Remove from heat
and add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce to taste, then
add mayonnaise.
Next,
use
hand
mixer
and add cream cheese.
Last, add green onions, celery and crab meat.
After mixing thoroughly, place in molding container or casserole and refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Very, very good!!!!!!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well and put on stove; let simmer for 35 minutes (do not boil).

title: praline cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter and sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients well.
Grease a cookie sheet and coat with flour.
Recoat the cookie sheet before each baking.
Drop batter by scant teaspoonfuls 5 inches apart, including a nut half each time.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook entire box of rice as per directions on box.
Mix together in casserole dish:
cooked rice, both soups, chicken and spices.
Cook in microwave on High power 15 minutes.

title: veal scaloppine ala marsala
directions: Cover veal with flour, salt and pepper.
Saute in butter until brown (3 to 5 minutes).
Remove veal from pan.
Keep warm in oven. In frying pan saute onions and mushrooms.
Add wine and cook slowly until wine is almost evaporated.
Add beef broth, chopped parsley and browned cutlets.
Simmer 7 to 8 minutes each side.
Serve immediately.

title: ma-maw's butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons warm water. Mix sugar, shortening,
1 cup water, salt and eggs. Stir in yeast and flour; chill overnight.

title: relish
directions: Rather than grind the first four items, these can be put through a food processor.
However, chop the celery very fine. Combine everything in large kettle.
Bring to full rolling boil over high heat.
Pack in canning jars, cap with sterilized lids. Set aside until cool.
Check to see if they seal.
If any jars are not, open, reheat and cap again with new lid.
Will keep 2 years on shelf, away from sun.

title: spinach and mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine the meat, soup mix, bread crumbs and eggs.
Shape into a 10 x 10-inch square on a sheet of waxed paper.
Combine spinach with cheeses; spread over beef mixture, leaving a 1-inch border.
Roll, jelly roll style, removing waxed paper while rolling.
Seal edge tightly.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, place meat loaf seam side down.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: tomato chow chow
directions: Chop, mix and let stand overnight. Fill jars and cook in hot water bath for 25 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with flour and brown on both sides.
Add vegetables.
Pour chili sauce over all.
Fill bottle with water and pour over all.
Simmer about 3 hours.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Before baking sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti noodles into thirds.
Cook and drain with cold water.
Add Italian dressing and Schilling Salad Supreme spice. Add fresh vegetables.
Any combination works great.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place melted butter in a Pyrex dish; add the beaten eggs and the 2 cans of corn (do not drain).
Add the onion, green pepper and the corn bread mix.
Mix all the ingredients together until smooth and creamy.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat with mixer until orange slices are chopped up.
Pour into 3 layer pans that have been greased and floured or use long pan. Cook as directed on cake mix box.
Test with toothpick.
Cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add alternately the flour, baking powder, baking soda and buttermilk. Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie stick flat on aluminum pizza pan.
Prick holes in top.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, then spread on cooked, cooled cookie dough.
Arrange sliced fruit on top.
Mix preserves and water and spoon over fruit.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in pie plate.
Pour chili on cream cheese. Sprinkle a little Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cream cheese is melted.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add the liquid from the blueberries and pineapple.
Stir in blueberries and pineapple. Pour into a long, shallow pie plate or dish.
Cover and chill until firm.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla until smooth.
Spread on top of congealed salad.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut each slice of bread into 5 sticks.
Place sticks on a cookie sheet and toast in a 250° oven for 30 minutes or until browned.
Mix peanut butter and Wesson oil in top of a double boiler.
Dip each stick into the peanut butter mixture and coat with graham cracker crumbs.
Let cool completely and store in tins.
Yields 30.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: The amounts of the ingredients are left up to your own personal taste. This recipe never tastes the same way twice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, shortening and bananas.
Add dry ingredients (flour, salt and soda).
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and let jell.
Break an angel food cake into pieces and stir into jello mixture.
Top with whipped cream and put back into refrigerator.
This is a large recipe and can be cut in half.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream sugar with eggs, oil and vanilla.
Sift flour with soda and salt; blend with creamed mixture.
Stir in cereal, coconut, nuts and chips.
Drop by a teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: grandma horton's "white linament"
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shake well and put in a bottle with a cap on it.
My uncle tells me Granny cherished her "capped bottle"!

title: stir-fry shredded beef a la henry
directions: Sprinkle beef with 2 teaspoons oil, sherry, cornstarch, baking soda, soy sauce and sugar.
Set aside for 30 minutes.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil in pan and add 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir in onion and stir-fry 2 minutes. Add green peppers and fry for 2 minutes. Remove from pan.
Heat remaining 3 tablespoons oil in same pan. Add beef.
Stir-fry until color changes.
Add a pinch of ground pepper and return vegetables to pan.
Mix well and stir-fry for 1 minute.

title: pig-pickin cake
directions: Mix
together cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges.
Bake in 3 layer
pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Pour orange juice over hot cake.
Let cool and frost, if desired.

title: party cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in hot water, add flour and salt; stir constantly until forms ball that won't separate.
Remove from heat and cool. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until smooth.
Drop from teaspoon 2 1/2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then 325° for 20 minutes.
Pop open and fill with chicken salad.

title: brunch potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in baking dish and mix in minced onion.
Mix soup and sour cream and spread on top.
Spread grated cheese on top. Crush corn flakes and put in saucepan with enough butter to mix. Put corn flakes on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Cream vanilla, cream cheese, sugar and oleo together.
Unroll pumpkin and spread with mixture (I do mine while it is still a little bit warm, works best.)
Re-roll and refrigerate.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook, debone and chop chicken; save broth.
Cook potatoes, carrots and onion until done.
Drain vegetables if you have a lot of liquid.
Add vegetables to chicken and broth.
Add cream of chicken soup and salt and pepper.
If you choose to use noodles, add them last.
Cook just until noodles are tender.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Stir together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; blend in. Form in 1 inch balls. Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pour pie filling in buttered casserole dish. Mix cake, nuts and margarine until crumbly. Spread on pie filling. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage bread
directions: Follow	 directions
for
mix;	let
rise
minutes. Spread dough
out
like
pizza.
Roll 1/4 inch thick.
Spread with cheeses,
sausage,	onion,	green
pepper and mushrooms. Sprinkle garlic
powder (go easy).
Roll and tuck corners in. Shape into ring.
Place on greased cookie sheet, whip egg and brush on
top. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30
minutes. Serve
sliced for brunch, potluck or for any occasion.
It's scrumptious!!!

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil. Shape into 4 patties. Refrigerate until firm.
Heat oil (1 inch) in frypan and fry patties until golden brown on both sides, 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel and serve.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix all ingredients except Ritz crackers and margarine.
Place mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cracker crumbs over top and drizzle melted margarine over crumbs.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: hootenanny pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan until bubbly.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and flour suing a blender or mixer and add the mixture to hot pan with butter.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until puffed.
Serve with syrup or Strawberry Sauce.

title: cajun shrimp gumbo
directions: To make a roux, heat oil in a large cast-iron skillet.
When very hot, but not smoking, add 1/2 the flour.
Stir constantly with a wire whisk.
Add remaining flour.
Stir rapidly until dark and smooth (don't burn).
Add vegetables and cook until tender. Add tomato sauce, 2 cups water and chicken broth.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients except rice.
Simmer 15 minutes. Serve over rice.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: marmalade dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in marmalade, sour cream, pecans and cinnamon.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak in very thin strips.
Brown quickly in butter in hot skillet.
Stir in water, soup mix and mushrooms.
Cover.
Simmer, stirring only once or twice, for 1 hour, until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and tomato sauce.
Serve with hot rice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine the sugar and cornstarch. Stir in water until smooth. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Remove from the heat and stir for 2 minutes. Remove from the heat. Add the gelatin and the lemon juice. Stir until dissolved. Allow to cool to room temperature, about 30 minutes. Add the strawberries and stir gently to coat. Spoon into the pastry shell. Chill until set, about 3 hours. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy gooey rolls
directions: Mx 1/4 cup sugar with the cinnamon.
Put frozen rolls in a tube pan and sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet cream biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into small biscuits.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pumpkin-vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until translucent.
Add chicken broth and heat to boiling.
Add potato, carrots, celery, lima beans, corn and beans.
Cover and cook over low heat until the vegetables are just tender, about 15 minutes.
Add pumpkin, nutmeg and pepper.
Increase heat and bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cream and heat through.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 servings.

title: shrimp - new orleans
directions: Saute onion, celery, green pepper and mushrooms in butter with seasonings.
Add tomatoes, paste and water.
Simmer a few minutes over low heat.
Place mixture in a casserole and stir in shrimp. Bake in moderate oven 30 minutes.
Serve with white rice.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter; add flour and stir until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk and half and half; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly. Add next 6 ingredients. Serve over rice.

title: easy baked chicken and dressing
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Mix soup of choice with milk in a separate bowl.
Dip chicken in soup mixture and roll in stuffing. Bake in single layer at 350° until chicken is done, when juice runs clear when pierced.
Serves 4.
Just double recipe for a large family.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Put all in crock-pot.
Cook on low 12 hours.

title: pineapple-chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add to juice the cornstarch, mustard, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic (sliced) and jelly.
Place skinned breasts layered in Pam coated baking dish.
Broil ten minutes at 400° until brown on top. Remove when browned.
Arrange pineapple around browned chicken. Spoon sauce over chicken and pineapple chunks.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple icebox dessert
directions: Lightly grease an 8-inch square cake pan.
Pack half of crushed wafers in bottom.
In medium bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, beating well.
Drain pineapple very well. Keep syrup for sauce.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream just until well combined.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with rest of crumbs.
Cover with foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve with following sauce, if desired.

title: caramel candy
directions: Butter sides and bottom of heavy saucepan with butter.
Add sugar and 1 cup cream.
Cook while stirring till soft ball stage (forms a ball when dripped in cup of cold water).
Slowly add second cup of cream as mixture boils and you stir.
Cook to soft ball stage again.
Slowly add the third cup of cream as you cook and stir.
Cook to soft ball stage again.
Add vanilla and nuts. Stir until it begins to thicken.
Pour in a buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: bonnie bonilla's apple pie(this is an award winning recipe)
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until mixture is crumbly. Add the other ingredients and stir until just blended.
Chill at least 1 hour.
(Dough can be refrigerated for up to 2 weeks.) Divide dough into 2 balls.
Roll each and lay one into pie pan. Set the other aside for top crust.
(I prefer to roll the dough on a cloth; a pillow case is perfect.
Just flour it and roll.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) prepared graham cracker crusts.
Drizzle chocolate syrup or chocolate curls on top.
Freeze for 8 hours before serving.
I keep some made in freezer for a quick dessert!

title: beef 'n corn casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add soup and cream cheese; stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Add corn, pimento and seasonings; mix lightly.
Pour
into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with biscuit halves (cut in half crosswise), placed cut side down.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until biscuits are brown.
Serves 6.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix and spread onion and sour cream in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Add sauerkraut.
Crumble corned beef over sauerkraut. Add Swiss cheese.
Top with crumbled rye bread.
Drizzle 1/2 pound or less melted margarine over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy squares
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until light. Add eggs and vanilla, then flour, salt and baking powder, sifted together.
Mix well. Spread in greased pan. Spread on top of cake a mixture of the egg white, nuts and brown sugar.
Add sugar gradually to the egg white while beating until stiff. Fold in the chopped nuts. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Cut in squares while hot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper; dip lightly in flour. Place in skillet, using shortening or Crisco, and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel and set aside.
Then layer potatoes in long Pyrex dish and add diced onion; salt and pepper the potatoes. To this layer, add the pork chops and pour mushroom soup over this. Then add milk over all ingredients.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: seafood louis dressing
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Serve with chilled seafood salad.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken-n-biscuit
directions: Pressure cook chicken for 15 minutes; cool and pick meat off bone.
Mix broth, chicken, butter, 1 cup milk and salt.
Place on stove and bring to a boil.
Mix 1 cup milk, Crisco and flour; make biscuits.
Pour chicken and gravy in square baking pan with biscuits on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: speedy rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and oil.
Add flour gradually.
Beat with mixer.
Let rise until double in bulk. Punch down and shape as desired.
Let rise.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed meat loaf(serves 6)
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and catsup.
On a sheet of wax paper, spread mixture in a 9 x 12-inch rectangle, or until meat is about 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Using the wax paper to start, roll the meat, starting at the smaller end.
Place seam-side down in 2-quart baking dish on a meat rack (to keep meat out of juices).
Cook in microwave oven, uncovered, for 14 to 16 minutes on full power; turn once during cooking time. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate mousse angel cake
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Drizzle with rum and set aside.
Melt chocolate over low heat in a double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until smooth.
Add vanilla and a dash of salt.
Whip 1 cup whipping cream until stiff and fold into chocolate mixture.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain, cool, peel and cut into cubes.
Toss potatoes lightly with salt, pepper, celery salt, parsley and onion.	Brown bacon until crisp.
Drain from skillet all but 1 tablespoon bacon fat.
Stir in flour until smooth. Gradually add vinegar and water.
Stir in sugar.
Bring to boiling point, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add potato mixture.
Toss lightly.
Serve warm.

title: grandma dunham's all season potato salad
directions: Boil and cook potatoes and eggs and let cool.
Chop or mince onions.
Drain cans of peas and beans.
Peel and dice or chunk potatoes.
Shell eggs and dice.
Put into large bowl.
Add drained peas and string beans.
Add desired amount of salad dressing or mayonnaise, stirring gently until mixed.
Let chill in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish and serve cold.

title: cashew nut loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a medium sized bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Stir before using. Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: chinese velvet chicken soup with sweet corn
directions: Mince chicken.
Mix well with sherry, salt and beaten egg whites.
Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add corn and chicken mixture.
Bring to a boil again.
Serve hot.
Garnish with green onions.

title: zucchini corn-fetti
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter; add zucchini, onion and green pepper and cook until zucchini is tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in corn, basil and pepper and heat thoroughly.
Add cheese and heat until cheese is melted.
Pour into serving dish and garnish with tomato wedges.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: french toast
directions: Beat egg with milk.
Add spices.
Dip bread in mixture and fry in butter.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: icebox oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal.
Form in roll.
Store in icebox overnight or longer.
Slice thin; bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: blueberry-orange bread
directions: Dry rinsed blueberries.
Place grated orange rind, sugar, water and salt in saucepan.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cool somewhat. Measure and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.

title: curried chicken and artichoke salad
directions: Cook both rice mixtures according to directions. Cool.
In a large bowl, combine rice, chicken, bell pepper, olives, scallions and drained artichokes.
In a separate bowl, mix together marinade, mayonnaise, curry, salt and pepper.
Stir mixture into chicken salad. Refrigerate. Serves 10 to 12.

title: refrigerator  rolls
directions: Heat Crisco and milk; pour over sugar and salt and stir well. Dissolve yeast in water.
Beat egg slightly and add to Crisco-milk mixture.
Combine the two mixtures and stir in flour. With lightly greased hands, mold dough into a ball.
Place in bowl rubbed with Crisco and store in refrigerator.
About 3 1/2 hours before baking, knead and make into rolls.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hours).
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet yogurt dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve cold.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix taco seasoning and Miracle Whip; cover and refrigerate. Brown hamburger and part of onions.
Rinse well and cool.
Mix lettuce, tomatoes, remainder of the onion, 1 1/2 cups cheese, hamburger and seasoning mixture.
Top with the remainder of cheese.
Add black olives and sour cream if desired.
Serve with corn chips.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown onion and beef in skillet.
Drain.
Mix noodles according to package directions.
Add to hamburger.
Add drained vegetables, soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir until well mixed.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with shredded cheese and bread stuffing. Heat until hot and bubbly and cheese is melted, about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable risotto
directions: In a 3-quart pan, saute 1/2 cup sliced zucchini, 1/2 cup mushrooms, 1/2 cup chopped red bell peppers, 1/2 cup chopped onion, 1 teaspoon chopped basil and 1 clove garlic in 2 teaspoons vegetable oil on medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add 1 cup uncooked rice and cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in half can chicken broth and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes or until broth is absorbed. Stir in the rest of broth, stirring until absorbed.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cook more.
Add cheese after water is absorbed.

title: cream cheese tuna dip
directions: Cube cream cheese in a blender; add peppers, onion and hot sauce. Blend well. Add tuna and stir well. Refrigerate before serving. Serve with crackers.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients in medium bowl.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Chocolate chips or nuts may be added.

title: pork tenderloin with mushroom sauce
directions: Brown
tenderloins that have been coated with salt, pepper, thyme and flour.
Saute onion and celery in pan that meat was browned in.
Place meat and all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Then stir and thicken with Wondra flour if needed.
Bake uncovered about 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients
except soup.
Put in casserole and top with creamed chicken soup.
Bake
1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breasts wellington
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form and fold into rice.
Pound chicken with meat mallet.
Sprinkle each side with salt and pepper.

title: lime-cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and let partially set.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex. Chill until set.

title: sandy's caramel corn
directions: Spread in a large pan the popcorn.
Put this in a very low oven at 250° to keep warm and crisp. Combine in a 2-quart heavy pan the butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Place these ingredients on medium heat until sugar dissolves. Continue to boil to firm ball stage (240°) about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the soda.
Syrup will foam.
Take popped corn from the oven and pour hot caramel mixture over it in a fine stream.
Stir to mix well. Return to oven for 45 to 50 minutes, stirring well every 15 minutes. Cool and serve or store.
Makes 5 quarts or 2 pounds.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Line bottom of glass square dish with graham crackers. Prepare pudding mix as directed on package for pudding.
Let stand 5 minutes, then blend whipped topping.
Spread half of pudding over crackers, put a layer of crackers, then pour rest of pudding over crackers. Put crackers over pudding. Pour pie filling on top. Chill 3 hours.

title: charlie gibson's enchilada casserole
directions: For the topping, set aside sour cream, 1/2 cup of the grated cheese and 2 cups of the Doritos. Take remaining Doritos and crumble with your hands into mixing bowl. Mix in remaining ingredients, except those reserved for the topping, and place in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch casserole dish. Bake for 20 minutes at 375°. Remove casserole from oven. Spread on sour cream. Cover with Doritos and sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese. Bake for an additional 5 minutes and serve.

title: spanish corn
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together.
Add mandarin oranges, marshmallows, pecans and bananas.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Line baking pan with whole vanilla wafers.
Pour condensed Eagle Brand milk in mixing bowl.
Add juice of lemons.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Add drained mandarin oranges to milk mixture.

title: quick sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands.
Shape loosely into small balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet or freeze and bake when needed.

title: homemade orange sherbet
directions: Mix milk and Orange Crush.
Pour into electric ice cream churn.
Churn until firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mix and blend thoroughly.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in 2 prepared pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: tallerine
directions: Brown beef, onions and chopped bell pepper.
Add all other ingredients, except noodles and cheese.
Boil noodles until tender.
Drain.
Layer meat, noodles and cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350°.

title: fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, reserving 1/4 cup.
Mix well.
Add lemon extract.
Mix reserved flour with fruit; add fruit and pecans to mixture.
Bake in a lightly greased tube pan for 2 hours and 30 minutes at 250°. Yield:
20 servings.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and beef, saving 1/4 cup beef for top of cheese ball.
Combine all ingredients except the 1/4 cup beef and shape into ball.
A double recipe makes a better size ball.

title: 3-meal pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat skillet coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Use approximately 1/4 cup batter for each pancake. Flip when bubbles appear on top.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together; let set for 1 hour or more.
Serve onto crisp lettuce leaf.

title: water-bath method for pickling and canning
directions: Begin by making sure that the pot or kettle you are using is deep enough that you can place the canning jars inside it and cover them with at least 1-inch of water.

title: mystery mini loaves
directions: Soak breadcrumbs in milk.
Add beaten egg and soup mix.
Stir well. add ground beef, salt and pepper to taste. shape into mini loaves.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over meat loaves.
Bake at 350° until meat is done, 45 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Brown bacon; drain and set aside.
In bacon fat, add onions and cook until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add vinegar, sugar, water, salt and celery seed.
Cook until thickened.
Fold in potatoes, eggs and parsley.
Heat.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Slice thin enough potatoes to fill a two-quart casserole dish. Grease dish with butter.
Place half of the potatoes and onions in bottom of dish.
Mix Cheddar cheese soup and milk together.
Pour half over potatoes and onions.
Place the rest of potatoes and onions in dish and pour remaining soup over this.
Dot with butter. Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and cook for 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Cook sweet potatoes.
Peel.
Save water.
Mix water, milk, salt, sugar and butter or margarine.
Heat until butter is almost melted.
Add to yeast, cinnamon, nutmeg, cooked sweet potatoes, oats and about 3 cups flour.
Mix. Add remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add salt, pepper, onion and chops. Brown lightly on both sides.
Place potatoes in baking dish. Arrange chops over potatoes.
Add soup and milk to skillet.
Blend and pour over chops.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, covered. Uncover and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer, until potatoes are done.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1 cup powdered sugar and melted butter; press into baking dish.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Cook slow until heated.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cook rice and let cool. Wash and cut the tops out of the bell peppers.
Mix the ground chuck, cooked rice, onions and whatever amount of the other ingredients you want completely.
Stuff this into the bell peppers.
Wrap into aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour or until peppers are done.
Cut bell peppers in half and top with grated cheese.

title: fresh strawberry salad
directions: Wash, dry and tear leaf lettuce.
Wash, hull and quarter strawberries.
Peel and slice kiwi.
Toss all gently in a bowl. Combine remaining ingredients in a shaker.
Shake until well mixed.
Just before serving, drizzle shaker dressing over salad ingredients.
Serves 4.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Sprinkle sugar on kraut first, then add rest of ingredients. Combine and chill 24 hours.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine margarine, flour and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and half of the Cool Whip; blend well.
Spread over cooled crust.
Chill.
Combine pudding mixes and milk; beat 2 minutes with rotary beater at medium speed. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread with remaining Cool Whip. Garnish with pecans and chocolate.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.

title: 1st place state fair cornbread
directions: In mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs and milk. Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Bake at 400° for 22 to 27 minutes. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: dark fudge
directions: Melt chips over low heat.
Add condensed milk and salt. Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spread on wax paper. Chill 2 hours.
Store at room temperature.

title: stuffed fish
directions: Season fish with seasoning salt, black pepper and seafood seasoning or sage.

title: grandma ammons' boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil water, sugar, shortening and raisins for 2 minutes.
When cooled to lukewarm, add all dry ingredients to raisin mixture. Bake at 350°
until done.

title: davy crockett cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Blend together the shortening, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.

title: squash casserole
directions: Thaw and drain squash.
Cook.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° until warm throughout.

title: venison stew
directions: Season meat; brown slowly in oil, then simmer until meat is tender (add just a little water).
Then add all other ingredients and cook for about 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Serve over rice.

title: plain sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Make into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of glass in sugar and mash each cookie out.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Place 1 tablespoon oil in a heavy saucepan.
Add 1 medium chopped onion, the ground beef and 1 teaspoon salt.
Brown the meat well; set aside.
Cook together the tomato juice and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add the cooked meat; pour over drained spaghetti.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs and maple flavoring; beat well and add flour.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet and press down with a fork.
Cookies may also be dropped by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and pressed down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Mix cookies with margarine.
Save aside 2/3 cup for topping. Put rest of cookie mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice 1/2 of ice cream over crumbs.
Drizzle 1/2 cup syrup over ice cream. Sprinkle 1/3 cup crumbs.
Add rest of ice cream and 1/2 cup syrup. Top with Cool Whip and 1/3 cup crumbs.
Cover with foil and freeze several hours.

title: 1st class chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together except crumbs and margarine.
Melt margarine. Add bread crumbs; sprinkle over top. Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tarragon chicken salad
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer on a large jelly roll pan. Cover evenly with heavy cream.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.
Shred chicken into bite size pieces in a large bowl.
Wisk sour cream and mayonnaise together and pour over chicken.
Add remaining ingredients and toss well*.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Use a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Tear up bread; pour melted margarine over it and stir together.
Use a saucepan, heat tomatoes, salt and brown sugar to boiling.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and roll in crushed pecans.

title: boiled seafood cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except milk; form into patties.
Coat with milk powder and broil until brown.

title: carrots
directions: Chop onions and green pepper; saute in oleo.
Add parsley. Boil carrots until tender; drain and add to other ingredients. Add sugar; mix well.

title: fresh wahoo
directions: Place the wahoo steaks in a large bowl and sprinkle both sides with the celery salt. Pour the sweet almond oil over the steaks and cover tightly. Refrigerate for 1 hour minimum. Slice enough peppers and onion to cover each steak while baking. Preheat oven to 350°. Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes minimum. Filets should flake with a fork.

title: easy pralines
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and salt until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Beat until creamy and loses gloss. Stir in pecans. Working quickly, drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Store in box in layers of waxed paper.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Add honey, mustard and curry powder.
Place chicken in baking dish; baste with honey mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.

title: small mints
directions: Cook sugar, water and corn syrup in 2-quart pan.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to 232° without stirring.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat until creamy with wire whip.
Add a few drops of flavoring, oil and food coloring.
Drop from teaspoon on wax paper.
(Keep pan over hot water.)

title: chicken with orange
directions: Brown chicken pieces under broiler.
Place in casserole; sprinkle with paprika.
Arrange onion slices over chicken. Combine juice concentrate, brown sugar, parsley, soy sauce, ginger, water and sherry.
Pour over chicken and onion.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: crock-pot pork steak
directions: Brown steaks.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour cream of mushroom and cream of chicken over steaks.
Cook on medium for 4 to 6 hours.

title: washington cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift flour, measure and sift again with soda and salt. Cream margarine with both sugars, beat eggs into margarine - sugar mixture. Add vanilla and mix well. Stir in dry ingredients; add nuts, oats, and bits and mix all thoroughly. Drop on greased cookie sheet, (about 1 tablespoon batter for each cookie), and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° until light brown. Makes about 6 dozen delicious cookies.

title: manicotti shells
directions: Put everything together in a bowl and use mixer.
Put some parsley in a small pan.
Keep flame on medium.
Put 2 tablespoons of batter in pan to cover the bottom.
Cook one side and turn to do the other side.
When done, fill shell with Ricotta cheese.

title: red cocktail sauce
directions: In medium bowl, whisk all ingredients until combined.
Chill well before serving.
Makes 2 cups.

title: perfect peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches on bottom of 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to peaches and mix.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg; toss with fork until crumbly. Sprinkle over peaches.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until slightly browned.
Top with ice cream, if desired.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape in small balls. Brown.
Place in brown gravy or Italian sauce and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix well and freeze.

title: macaroni with marinated tomatoes
directions: Mix tomatoes, onions, garlic, parsley, salt, basil, pepper and oil.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, but no longer than 24 hours.
Prepare macaroni as directed on package; drain. Immediately toss with tomato mixture.

title: son-in-law soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Add corn and chicken.
Combine flour and egg until crumbly.
Add to boiling soup, stirring constantly. Simmer about 10 minutes.

title: pheasant and wild rice
directions: Brown cut up pheasant in hot oil.
Mix wild rice in bottom of roaster pan according to package directions.
Dot with butter. Add mushrooms.
Lay pheasant on top of rice after browning.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, syrup and salt.
Mix well; add vanilla and pecans.
Bake until firm, about an hour.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown chuck, onion, green pepper in frying pan and drain. Add pepperoni, mushrooms, spaghetti sauce, cheese.
Cook noodles, drain.
Mix all ingredients with noodles. Put in two 9 x 13 inch pans that have been sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Recipe can be halved for a small family or doubled for a large crowd.

title: hawaiian summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Toss just before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves or pineapple shells.

title: chocolate scotcharoos
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; cook until it boils.
Take off heat and stir in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Melt chips over hot water and spread over mixture. Chill 5 or 10 minutes.

title: chrusciki - bow ties
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, using enough flour so mixture does not stick to fingers.
Knead 1/2 hour.
Roll thin; cut into strips and make slits in center.
Pull one end through to make a bow.
Fry in deep hot fat; brown lightly.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Drop onto a cookie sheet and flatten a little.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 375°.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Combine pineapple and cheese.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Stir into pineapple mixture.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: noodle kugel(sweet pasta)
directions: Boil noodles according to package; drain.
In large bowl, add butter and sugar to noodles.
Beat eggs.
Add to sour cream.
Add to noodle mixture.
Add sliced apples, raisins, cinnamon, cottage cheese and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
If seems dry, add more cottage cheese and/or sour cream.
Pour into buttered, 2-quart pan.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: jambalaya
directions: Fill a large saucepan with water, bring to a boil, then add the allspice and drop in shrimp.
Lower the heat to simmer and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain and shell, then set aside.
In a Dutch oven, add
bacon
and
saute
over moderate heat for a minute until soft,
not brown.
Add onions and garlic and cook onions until soften.
Add	green
pepper, tomatoes, broth, bay leaf, thyme, Tabasco
sauce and Worcestershire sauce and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice gradually and bring to a boil.	Cover and simmer until
liquid
is
absorbed, about 45 minutes.
Add shrimp, more Tabasco sauce, pepper and salt if desired.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Tear cake in bite-size pieces.
Take 1 Cool Whip and mix with cake.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add 1 Cool Whip.
Combine the two mixtures.
Slice strawberries; mix 1 tablespoon sugar and glaze.
Layer cake mixture and strawberries with glaze.

title: beef-macaroni
directions: Brown ground chuck in a large skillet, stirring until it crumbles; drain beef.
Add water and next 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening. Add sugar; beat in egg and molasses. Mix all dry ingredients; add gradually to first mixture. Mix well. Place in refrigerator for about an hour, even overnight. Form a teaspoon (or tablespoon) of dough into balls. Roll in granulated sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Cool. Place in tightly covered tin.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add flour to make dough.
Roll out. Shape and put in a greased pan.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Grease 3 small loaf pans or 2 large pans.
Makes cupcakes too! Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: greek-style pita sandwiches
directions: Partially freeze lamb or pork.
Thinly slice across the grain into bite-size strips. Set aside.
Wrap pita halves in foil.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise or salad dressing and dill weed.
Set aside.

title: grits casserole
directions: In saucepan bring water and salt to boil.
Slowly stir in grits.
Reduce heat and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove grits from heat and add a small of amount of hot grits to eggs.
return to saucepan.
stir in sausage, 1 cup cheese, milk, and butter;
stir until the butter melts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until
top begins to brown.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: crispy cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Blend in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Divide dough in half.
Cover dough and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
You may blend in food colors with one half of the dough to make stained glass designs.
Roll dough to 1/8 inch thickness, and cut patterns from colored dough to place on top of cookies.
Bake on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° preheated oven for 7 to 8 minutes or until golden brown on edges.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in a gallon jar.
Mix vinegar, water, salt and sugar.
Stir and let stand while slicing cucumbers.
Slice onion; put on top of sliced cucumbers along with 1 garlic clove, pepper and mustard seed.
Pour liquid over and close.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: microwave quick fudge
directions: Butter 10 x 10-inch dish or line with foil.
In large bowl, melt butter, then add sugar and cocoa (which are sifted together) and milk.
Do not stir.
Place in microwave oven 2 1/2 minutes. Take bowl out of oven.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into dish.
Place in freezer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Peel, core and quarter apples.	Wrap each quarter in crescent roll.
Place in 9 x 9 sprayed square dish.	Sprinkle very liberally with cinnamon.
Combine remaining ingredients in pan and cook until sugar dissolved.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle more cinnamon on each roll.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let sit about 15 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Bring oil, vinegar, sugar and salt to a boil.
Let cool.
Pour over beans and place in refrigerator overnight or at least 4 hours.

title: tart shells
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Form into mini muffin pans and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Fill with chicken salad, ham salad, etc.

title: tiny party pizza
directions: Grate cheese, then mix all ingredients together.
Spread on bread rounds and put on a cookie sheet.
Put under the broiler 2 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes lots of appetizers.
The spread can be made ahead and frozen.
Remove from freezer several hours before needed.

title: yeast muffins
directions: Mix salt, sugar and yeast in 1 cup flour.
Melt butter in scalded milk.
Add to flour mixture and beat well.
Add beaten egg.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour and let rise in warm place 1 hour.
Stir down and spoon into greased muffin tins.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° until browned.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: primo pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except dressing in medium bowl.
Pour dressing over salad:
toss well.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Serve.
Makes 7 cups.

title: gooie butter cake
directions: Mix 1 egg and butter together; add cake mix.
Batter will be stiff.
Butter the bottom of a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Pat mixture in the bottom of the pan.
Mix together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour over mixture already in pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: green bell pepper casserole
directions: Halve or quarter green peppers and remove seeds.
Parboil 5 minutes; drain.
Brown onion and meat in fat.
Add tomatoes, corn and seasonings.
Place peppers around edge of casserole dish. Pour meat mixture in center of pepper ring.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Top with 4 to 5 slices of white bread, cubed and coated with melted butter.
Brown bread 10 to 15 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Chop celery and onion.
Mix all ingredients, except eggs and macaroni, in large bowl.
Cut up eggs.
Add eggs and macaroni to bowl.
Chill before serving.

title: hermits
directions: Sift flour, soda and spices together; set aside.
Mix shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and water.
Add beaten eggs, reserving one teaspoon eggs to coat top of Hermits.
Add flour mixture.
Fold in nuts and raisins.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat 5 large eggs; add corn, flour, sugar, salt and pepper. Warm milk in which margarine has been added.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After about 20 minutes, stir thoroughly.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and sugar.
Add 3 jars baby food.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: egg nasty
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the rest; pour it in.
Cook at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until puffy and slightly brown.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach; tear leaves into bite size pieces. Place in salad bowl.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Pour dressing over spinach; toss to coat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon; toss lightly.
Serves 4.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown beef and pork seasoned with pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
15 minutes before done, sprinkle top with sharp Cheddar cheese.
