title: easy mix brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together (flour, sugar, cocoa and salt). Cream shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Add dry ingredients to shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together.
Put in an 8-inch
greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown flour in oil, stirring to make smooth paste.
Add meat, salt, pepper, water and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Simmer 30 minutes or longer if needed until vegetables are no longer hard.

title: iced box fruit cake
directions: Combine milk and marshmallows into double boiler.
Cook until melted. Pour over ingredients and mix well.
Put in refrigerator. Let stand until set.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Layer:
graham crackers, pudding, graham crackers, pudding, graham crackers and chocolate icing.

title: white chili (tandi's version)(serves 2 to 3 people.  for larger crowds, just double or triple.)
directions: After cooking for short time, add chopped green chilies to taste and just before serving, add handful of shredded Monterey Jack cheese (about 1 pound).
Serve immediately with hot flour tortillas.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Combine onion, cabbage, tomato, peppers and salt; let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Combine sugar, celery seed, mustard seed, turmeric, vinegar and water; pour over drained vegetables. Simmer for 3 minutes.
Seal in pint jars while hot.
The mixture may also be cooled and frozen.

title: swedish bean and bacon soup
directions: Cook bacon in a 5-quart pot over medium heat 5 minutes or until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Saute onion in fat 4 minutes or until soft.
Add broth plus 1 extra cup water, the carrots, bacon, marjoram, allspice and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and boil gently 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Top servings with sour cream.

title: vickie's chicken and spaghetti
directions: Brown in skillet, margarine, onion and garlic.
Add chili powder, tomatoes, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Stir to mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add chopped chicken.
Cook spaghetti according to directions on package.
Place spaghetti in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over cooked and drained spaghetti.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and place in oven until cheese is melted.
Stir.
Garnish with more cheese if desired.

title: "sinful" pasta
directions: Melt butter in saute pan.
Add cream, basil, tomatoes, pepper, nutmeg, salt and cheese.
Saute for 3 minutes.

title: southern red rice
directions: Fry bacon; remove and place on paper towels.
Brown peppers and onions in drippings.
Add tomatoes, sauce and Tabasco.
Stir in rice and crumbled bacon.
Pour into greased casserole. Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onion soup and eggs like you would for meat loaf.
Use more bread crumbs if necessary.
Make into steak-shaped patties.
Dip in flour and brown on each side. Place in a greased baking dish.
Make a gravy of tomato soup and celery soup and 1 can water.
Pour over meat patties.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: meatless chili soup
directions: Drain garbanzo beans and corn.
Drain and rinse the kidney beans.
In a large saucepan, stir together the garbanzo beans, corn, kidney beans, broth, tomatoes, onion, chili powder, garlic, red pepper and pepper.
Bring mixture to boiling, then reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel, wash and grate the potatoes very fine. Mix the grated onion, eggs, flour and pinch of salt.

Add potatoes and mix well. Add oil to skillet and get hot. Drop mixture in by spoonful and flatten with fork. Fry on both sides until brown and crisp. Add more oil as needed. Serve with applesauce and lentil soup for a German flavor.

title: lipton oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag, add all ingredients and shake until evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into a large baking dish.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into strips, trimming fat; salt and pepper to taste. Coat with flour; place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour mushrooms, onion, green pepper and tomato sauce over steak.
Cover and cook on Medium for 45 minutes or until meat is tender, stirring once.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: june's fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit together; add vanilla pudding and mix well.
Goes well with June's chicken divan.

title: good doughnuts
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, soda, cream of tartar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a larger mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in melted shortening.
Add flour mixture and sour milk alternately to egg mixture; beat just until blended after each addition.
Cover; chill dough about 4 hours.

title: german pancakes
directions: Combine milk, flour, eggs and salt.
Melt butter in hot oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour batter into hot pan and bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: crater cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle pecans and coconut over baking dish. Prepare cake mix according to package directions and pour on top. Melt the cream cheese and butter over low heat. Stir in confectioners sugar and mix until blended. Pour over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: appetizer fruit combo
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving juice.
In a mixing bowl, combine pineapple chunks, melon balls and strawberries.
Combine the reserved pineapple juice and marmalade; pour over fruits. Stir gently.
Chill 1 to 2 hours; stir occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: easy smothered duck
directions: Mix soup and oleo and pour over ducks.
They can be put in the oven, covered, or in a crock-pot.
Turn ducks in mixture about once an hour.
It will take them approximately 3 hours to cook in the oven or all day in the crock-pot.
I cook them until they start coming off the bones.
You don't need any salt with this, because you don't dilute the soup.
You can add some pepper if you like.

title: lori's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken in seasoned water until done.
Debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Add pimentos, cheese, jalapeno sauce, mushrooms, mushroom soup and chicken broth as needed.
Pour in baking dish and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 35 to 50 minutes.

title: pull apart bread
directions: Thaw frozen dough for one hour, then cut into 1-inch cubes. Melt margarine; add sugar and cinnamon.
Dip cubes into mixture and place in greased Bundt pan.
Let rise 2 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Invert to cool.

title: chocolate-oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, margarine, milk and egg in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoons about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until almost no indentation remains in center.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and spices together; stir into pumpkin. Add Milnot and eggs.
Add nuts at this point, if used.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for another 25 to 30 minutes or until filling is firm (when knife inserted in pie comes out clean).
Garnish with whipped Milnot topping.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour, stirring after margarine melts.
Cover to cook.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all together in blender until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, blend in flour.
Add broth, milk and seasoning.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick.
Add chicken and vegetables and heat.

title: peanut butter balls covered in chocolate
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter; mix.
Add 10x sugar, graham cracker crumbs and vanilla.
Mix well and chill.
Roll into small balls and chill again.
Dip in melted chocolate and dry on waxed paper.
(Paraffin may be added to chocolate to make it firm.)

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion together; drain.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: chicken okowa
directions: Wash and then soak the mochi-gome for 8 hours.
Soak kampyo and shiitake for 1 hour.
Cut up chicken into small pieces, also the takenoko, gobo, kampyo and shiitake.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, soups and cheese.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: skillet goulash
directions: Brown beef, onion and peppers.
Add salt, pepper and garlic. After meat is thoroughly cooked, add 1 quart whole tomatoes. While meat is browning, bring the water to a boil for the macaroni in another pot.
Cook macaroni.
Add cooked macaroni to meat mixture.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel pie
directions: Caramelize the 3/4 cup sugar in heavy skillet over low heat. While this is caramelizing, mix all other ingredients.
Pour mixture into melted sugar in skillet and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Make meringue out of the 3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Brown in oven.

title: sondra's banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased bread pan and bake at 325° for 35 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic.
Drain off liquid.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Let cook for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumbers with dressing
directions: In small bowl combine the yogurt, scallions, salt, pepper and mustard.
Blend.
Add thinly sliced cucumbers and mix well to coat with dressing.
Lay about 2 or 3 dill sprigs on top but do not mix in.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings. Carbohydrate 8 g, protein 4.2 g, fat 1.1 g, calories 58.

title: frozen salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix with mayonnaise until smooth.
Add crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put in freezer for at least 24 hours.
Cut in cubes of desired size (take out of freezer long enough to soften slightly).
Serves 9 to 10.

title: steak ala jack
directions: Marinate 3/4-inch thick steak in 1/2 cup Jack Daniels, fresh parsley, chopped celery and whole mushrooms, for approximately 2 hours.
Then cook slowly with juice, adding approximately 2 tablespoons butter, 15 minutes on each side.
Serve with twice baked potatoes and salad.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add butter and cheese.
Stir in crumbs (save some for top) and lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cook slowly at 300° for 6 to 8 hours in crock-pot.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine oatmeal and water and set aside for 20 minutes. Cream together brown sugar, sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift together flour,
salt,
baking
soda
and cinnamon and add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to
40 minutes.
About 5 to 10 minutes before cake is done, make Brown Sugar Topping.

title: quick and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix.
Make into balls.
Put on cookie sheet.
Mash with a fork.
Bake.
Cookies should be done in eight minutes.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Shape into meatballs (makes 11 to 13 per pound).
Brown in 400° preheated oven for 10 minutes on each side in ungreased pan.
Then simmer in tomato sauce for 1/2 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble Oreos.
Spread 1/2 of them in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together Cool Whip, powdered sugar, margarine and cream cheese. In separate bowl, mix pudding mix, milk and vanilla. Combine mixtures.
Spread mixture over cookie crumbs. Top with remaining cookie crumbs.

title: quick fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar and cocoa in an 8x8 inch dish.
Pour in milk and place butter on top.
Cook in oven for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave oven and stir just to mix ingredients.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O in boiling water.
Add peach preserves and apricot
juice.
Pour
over
apricots
and	congeal.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions.
Combine cream cheese with Dream Whip and spread over top of jello mixture.

title: enchilada supreme
directions: Put cheese, onion and olives in separate dishes.
Brown meat, drain and set aside.

title: ricotta rice pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add rice.
Mix Ricotta, sugar, salt, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add to eggs and rice.
Blend all together.
Pour into greased 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: potatoes creamy
directions: Peel and chop up potatoes.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, blend milk and cream cheese.
Make sure this mixture is smooth. Put in chives, onion and salt.
Add the potatoes and stir well. Put the mixture into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can finish this dish on top of stove in a large pot. Watch carefully or it will boil over.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until golden brown.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Blend together.
Add cooked rice and broccoli.
Pour into a buttered baking dish or casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Crust cubes; mix ingredients together and chill.
Serve with veggies or chips.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Boil potatoes in saltwater until tender.
Add sausage, sauerkraut, onion, garlic, dill weed and caraway seed and bring to a boil.
Combine sour cream, flour and dill sprigs and stir in slowly.
Heat through; do not boil.
Season with salt and pepper and sugar if too tart.
Serve with dark bread.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pecan balls
directions: Grate or grind pecans fine.
Mix nuts, sugar, butter, vanilla, flour and salt in a bowl.
Work mixture thoroughly with hands until it holds together nicely.
Pinch off bits of dough and roll into balls.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 20 minutes at 350°.
Coat generously with confectioners sugar.

title: jalapeno black eyed peas & rice casserole
directions: Saut onion in butter until tender.
Add ground beef and brown. Stir in peas, rice, and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture onto a 2 qt. casserole.
Sprinkle cheese in over top.
Bake 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until cheese melt.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Place frozen rolls on cookie sheet.
Let rolls rise in a warm area.
After rolls have doubled in size, press roll flat.
Place 2 pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese in the center. Fold dough and place on cookie sheet.
Let rise again for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. Brush with butter and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Mix soda with sour cream and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Frost with chocolate frosting of your choice.
Serves 16.

title: de de's pumpkin walnut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir into mixture; add spices.
Add nuts and dates (both chopped well). Bake in 2 loaf pans or 3 (1 pound) cans, greased and floured, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together and pour into the pie shells.
Chill.

title: ella eders pot pie
directions: Roll on floured board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into squares.
Add to boiling broth.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook onion and celery in margarine; add cream of celery and potato soups.
Add clams.
Add cream and bacon.
Heat (do not boil) and serve.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix together meat, onion, bread crumbs, egg, 2 tablespoons ketchup, milk and seasonings.
Put in ring mold (plastic or glass microwavable).
Spread ketchup on top.
Microwave on High (10) for 18 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve with microwave baked potatoes and a tossed salad.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Let stand a few minutes. Drop by large spoons into hot oil.
Turn once. When brown, remove and drain. The flavor is improved if you let the batter set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: red jambalaya
directions: In a large skillet, saute on medium heat the
onion, bell pepper and green onion in olive oil.
In a 5-quart covered pot, add ingredients from skillet, then add the remaining ingredients. Cover with water 1/2 inch over.
Cover and cook most of water out, but leave moist.

title: pina colada squares(lo-cal)
directions: Heat pineapple juice to boiling; remove from stove.
In medium bowl, combine the gelatin with sweetener; mix.
Stir in hot pineapple juice until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch baking pan; chill until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt to taste, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions and place in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake covered at 375° for 20 minutes.
Unwrap crescent rolls and separate into 2 rectangles.
Press together perforated cuts and cut each rectangle lengthwise into 3 strips.
Place strips on casserole to form a crisscross lattice top.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 3 to 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: With electric mixer, mix sugar and Crisco. Add egg and vanilla. Add sifted self-rising flour. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and sugar briskly.
Set aside.
Layer large serving bowl, starting with lettuce, then chopped eggs, drained peas, chopped onion, bell pepper and cucumber.
Before pouring dressing on top, stir well.
Add and cover the top.
Sprinkle grated cheese on last.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid. Combine sugar and cornstarch. Stir in vinegar and beet liquid.
Stir over low heat until thick. Add beets and butter. Heat.
Serves 5.

title: nabisco pie
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 3/4 crushed wafers, all berries and Cool Whip.
Top with remaining wafers.

title: cream pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes or until pale yellow.
Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla, mixing until sugar is dissolved.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to batter alternately with cream.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: lazy woman's pickles
directions: Wash jar and lid good.
Wash cucumbers and pack tight.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Fill jar with water and shake good. Put on top of jar and tape tight.
Label and let set for 2 months (or longer) in cool place.

title: plum conserve
directions: Wash plums; remove stones and cut into pieces.
Peel and cut oranges into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in kettle and let come slowly to boiling point.
Cook until clear and thick. Place in jars and seal.

title: blueberry orange muffins
directions: Beat butter, sugar, eggs and yogurt until blended.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and rind.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt. Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until browned on edges.
Remove from sheet at once.
Makes about 18 macaroons.

title: no bake fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt in medium heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil-lined 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: polska kielbasa old country supper
directions: In heavy skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Add sliced potatoes, broccoli, carrots, celery and onions to bacon drippings.
Saute over medium heat.

title: whole earth buttermilk pancakes(fritters)
directions: *Can be made up of about 3/4 cup white flour, 1 cup wheat flour and 1/4 cup oatmeal and//or oat bran or wheat germ.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and add enough water to make 1 cup. Heat to boiling.
Pour over jello and dissolve.
Spoon in sherbet and stir until melted.
Stir in oranges and marshmallows.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until set.

title: quick 'n easy meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, onion and
egg;
shape into loaf.
Place on a sheet of foil.
Pour
mushroom
soup, undiluted, over the meat loaf. Loosely seal the
foil
and
place	on
a baking sheet. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
The soup mixes with the meat juices, creating a wonderful brown gravy.

title: mama naff's blueberry dessert
directions: Make a layer of graham cracker crumbs.
Mix together cream cheese and Dream Whip;
make layer over crumbs.
Make layer of pie filling.
Sprinkle with a few graham cracker crumbs for decoration.
May substitute cherry in place of blueberry filling.

title: struffli
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out into 1/2 inch thick rounds.
Cut into pieces and deep fry in 2 qt. very hot oil, until golden brown, drain and cool.
Heat honey until runny, add struffle, lower heat and allow struffle to absorb honey.
Pile in dishes, cool and top with sprinkles.
The amount of honey is to your taste, the more honey you use the sweeter the struffli will be.

title: chicken wraps
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut in desirable sizes.
Wrap crescent rolls around chicken pieces.
Place in oblong casserole dish (crescents not touching).
Mix soups, cheese and milk.
Heat soup mixture in microwave for about 5 minutes, stirring halfway through.
Pour over chicken wraps.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crescent tops are golden brown.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a 7 x 13-inch pan.
While still hot, spread pineapple and juice over top.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and pudding with milk.
Spread on cake.
Top with Cool Whip, coconut and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: easy raw broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli.
Chop finely.
Put in a large bowl and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine oil and lemon juice; pour over.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Peel tomatoes and cut into small pieces; discard seeds.
Add to broccoli.
Combine cream and mustard; pour over.
Mix well.
Spoon into lettuce cups and serve immediately.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt and gradually add hot milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; cool slightly.
Pour into pastry shell.
Cool.
Cover with meringue made of egg whites and 6 tablespoons of sugar.

title: coffee can strawberry ice cream
directions: Will also need one empty 1 pound coffee can with lid and 1 empty 32 ounce coffee can with lid.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce and water in small saucepan.
Simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened. Stir in pepper sauce.
Add meat.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook all ingredients, except green beans in crock-pot on high all day.
Add the green beans.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, chill and serve.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems; let dry. Mix cream cheese, Beau Monde (a spice mix) and bacon bits together. Use a table knife to "stuff" cream cheese into mushrooms. Bake on an ungreased cookie pan at 350° until cream cheese is lightly browned on top. Cool a moment before eating.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, brown sugar, granulated sugar, egg, water and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and soda.
Add flour mixture with shortening mixture.
Blend in oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Stir meal into rapidly boiling milk.
Cool until very thick, stirring constantly, to prevent burning.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
The mixture will be cold and very stiff.
Add well beaten eggs, salt, baking powder and melted butter.
Beat with electric mixer for 15 minutes.

title: creamy potluck potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, cook potatoes, covered in enough boiling salted water to cover, for 10 to 12 minutes or until just tender. Drain and rinse with cold water.

title: pork and potato main dish
directions: Brown steaks in skillet; place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place potato slices evenly over meat; put cheese over potatoes.
Pour soup over top of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately one hour or until meat and potatoes are tender.

title: dark caramel pecan rum sauce
directions: Place the cream cheese and heavy cream in a mixing bowl and beat with a whisk until smooth.
Set aside.
Place the sugar and water in a heavy saucepan over medium heat.

Stir just to dissolve the sugar, then let the mixture cook without stirring until it caramelizes (300° on a candy thermometer), 8 to 10 minutes. Remove the pan from the heat and pour in the cream mixture; it will sputter.
Then, over low heat, whisk the mixture just until smooth.
Stir in the rum and pecans (this will hold well, covered in refrigerator for 5 to 7 days).
Reheat over very low heat, stirring often.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Did You eat your five fruits

title: elephant ears
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Melt shortening and set aside.
Stir flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl.
Stir in milk and 3 tablespoons of melted shortening until soft dough forms.
Sprinkle a surface lightly with flour; turn dough onto the surface and knead 10 times. Roll dough into a 9 x 5-inch rectangle.
Brush with remaining melted shortening.
Sprinkle with mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Roll dough up tightly, beginning at narrow end.
Pinch edge of dough into roll to seal.
Cut into 4 equal pieces with a sharp knife.
Place cut sides up on cookie sheet and pat each into a 6-inch circle.
Sprinkle with more sugar.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and let cool.
Makes 4 ears.

title: skillet potatoes and onions
directions: Slice potatoes thinly.
Pour enough oil into skillet to cover bottom generously.
Make a layer of potatoes, followed with onion, spices and end with layer of potatoes on top.
Put grated cheese over potatoes.
Put foil over skillet and cook on low heat for 40 minutes.
If done when tested, place plate over pan and flip over. Cook, loosely covered, for 15 minutes.
Serve hot while freshly cooked.

title: butternut cake
directions: Beat all together for 10 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven. Turn heat to 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Add one box frozen spinach, thawed.
Mix together and bake at 250° for one hour.

title: barbecued chicken with glaze
directions: In large screw-top jar combine tomato sauce, olive oil, orange juice, vinegar, oregano, salt, peppercorns and garlic.
Cover and shake vigorously to blend in.
In shallow dish pour tomato sauce mixture over chicken.
Cover and marinate 2 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator, turning occasionally. Drain, reserving marinade.
Grill chicken over medium coals for 45 to 50 minutes, brushing with marinade and turning frequently. Just before serving, brush with a mixture of honey and mustard to glaze.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except stuffing) .
Grease a casserole dish and add stuffing like a pie crust.
Add squash mixture.
Dot
with butter.
Sprinkle the top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: mexican cakes
directions: Mix well and roll in small balls, size of walnut.
Bake at 400° for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Reese's chips.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan. Cool at room temperature.

title: frozen pumpkin dessert
directions: In a medium bowl combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in pecans.
In a large chilled bowl, fold pumpkin mixture into softened ice cream.
Place 1 cup cookie crumbs in bottom of a glass serving dish.
Spread half of the ice cream mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Reserve some for the top.
Spoon on the rest of the ice cream mixture. Sprinkle top with some cookie crumbs.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Freeze until firm, about 5 hours.
Garnish with sliced kiwi, raspberries or other fruit or berries.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crust:
Melt butter; mix with crackers.
Pat into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: grandma's lye soap
directions: Place all in a large cast kettle and boil for 1 hour.
Turn into shallow crocks; cool and the next day, cut into bars.

title: applesauce pound cake
directions: Beat butter in a large mixing bowl at medium speed of an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy. Gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears. Combine applesauce and soda and set aside.
Combine 2 3/4 cups flour and spices.
Add to butter mixture alternately with applesauce mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed just until blended after each addition.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup flour, raisins, and pecans.
Fold into batter. Pour batter into a greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan, and cool completely on wire rack.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brown beef with onion.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Alternate layers of tortillas, meat, sauce, beans and cheese in a casserole dish. Add water and cover. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: ugly cake
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Scatter pecans over mixture and press.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Fold in chocolate chips and pour over mixture
on top of other layer. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until center is golden brown. Cut into squares when cool.

title: exotic pie
directions: Mix together flour and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and at 300° for 10 minutes or until set.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; cream in peanut butter.
Add eggs and vanilla and stir well.
Then add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Press flat with fork. Bake at 350° or 325° until light brown.
Do not overbake.

title: easy steak marinade
directions: Combine ingredients in small bowl, stirring to blend.
Use to marinate steaks.
Marinate for several hours, turning occasionally.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth and creamy.
Serve with slices of tart apples.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken in 375° oven until done.
Cut into bite-size pieces and spread onto bottom of casserole dish.
Prepare stuffing as directed.
Spread over top of chicken.
Mix soups together and spread onto stuffing in casserole dish.
Crumble enough Ritz crackers to cover top of casserole dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Soak raisins in pineapple juice and pineapple for several hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a separate bowl, cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in jam.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in fruit mixture and pecans.
Pour into paper-lined 9 x 13 x 2 inch baking pan.
Bake for 50-55 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool.
Dust with confectioner's sugar before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil macaroni as directed, cold rinse and drain.
When cool, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Add all remaining ingredients, cover and chill overnight.
Serves 8 or more.

title: easy ice cream punch
directions: Place semi-thawed sherbet in large punch bowl.
Add Sprite or 7-Up and stir.
Makes a fluffy white punch.
For color, may add large can Hi-C punch or different flavor sherbet.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Combine whole wheat flour, 1 cup white flour, yeast and salt; mix well.
Heat water, milk, honey and shortening to about 120° (warm in microwave using temperature probe).
Add to flour mixture. Add egg and beat on high for 3 minutes.
Stir in enough of remaining white flour to make stiff dough.
Turn onto floured surface and knead for 5 minutes, until no longer sticky.
Put into greased bowl, cover and let raise until double (takes about 1 hour).
Punch down.
Divide into two.
Shape into loaves. Put into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Let raise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cinnamon crispas
directions: Cut tortillas into quarters. Brush butter on tortillas.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle onto tortillas. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until crisp.

title: very-cheesy macaroni
directions: In medium saucepan, cook macaroni per package directions until slightly firm.
Drain well.
Fill another saucepan 3/4 full with water.
Bring to a boil.
Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to medium and cook until slightly firm.
Drain well and set aside.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until done.
Mix with barbecue sauce. Press biscuits into greased muffin pan, bottom and sides.
Spoon hamburger on top of biscuits.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake biscuits as directed on can.

title: pineapple carrot bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Add carrots, oil, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Stir into the dry ingredients just until moistened.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until loaves test done.
Cool 10 minutes in pans before removing to wire racks.
Cool completely.

title: italian shredded beef for sandwiches
directions: The night before serving, place roast and beef cubes and 1/2 cup water in a crock-pot.
In the morning add 1/2 pkg.
mix, vinegar, oregano and garlic salt; cook all day.
Before serving, tear meat into shreds with 2 forks.
Serve on hard rolls and sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: mandy's lite dessert
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Fold fruit into Cool Whip.
Fold a sprinkle of orange flavor jello until entire contents of package are blended.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with cherries or nuts.

title: holiday hot wassail
directions: Place cranberry juice and apple juice in large electric percolator.
Put spices in basket.
Perk and serve.
A Parrish holiday tradition!

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Generously butter a 10-inch cast iron skillet.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by package directions and drain.
Mix with all remaining ingredients, except crackers.
Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: ham spread
directions: Let your cream cheese reach room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Serve.
Can be used for sandwiches or as a dip with crackers.

title: judy's corn casserole
directions: Drain and blot corn.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together cheese, sour cream, soup and onions.
Pour over corn.
On top put crushed Ritz crackers which have been tossed with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix everything in one large bowl.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Chop very small and combine ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: crusty spam bake
directions: Combine cornflakes crumbs, brown sugar and cloves. Slice spam into 8 slices.
Spread each side with mustard, then coat generously with crumb mixture.
Top with pineapple slices and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 with 2 slices each.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Stir spices into brown sugar.
Combine with liquids and heat to boiling.
Pour into cups with 1/2 tsp. butter and add cinnamon stick for stirring.
Keep a mixture of this recipe in the refrigerator to heat, one cup at a time.

title: calico corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and mix onion, pepper and pimiento with them.
Blend eggs, milk and melted shortening and stir into dry ingredients just long enough to mix.
Fold in cheese and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400° in a well-greased muffin pan. Muffins freeze well.

title: cranberry banana bread
directions: Do not preheat the oven for this recipe!
Melt the butter, then combine it with beaten eggs, mashed bananas, vanilla and water in a large mixing bowl.
Add the cake mix, and beat on medium speed for about 4 minutes.
Stir in the cranberry sauce, beating to break up large lumps.
Bake at 350° in a 10-inch tube pan (40 minutes) or 2 loaf pans (30 minutes).

You may need to turn the oven to 400° for the last 10 minutes to brown the bread. Instead of cranberry sauce, you may also add raisins or nuts. This is a moist, delicious bread that is easy to make and tastes even better when refrigerated.

title: baked ziti carey style
directions: Boil noodles, cook hamburger, onion, pepper and salt.
Mix together with spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, clams, oregano and garlic salt.
Get baking pan and layer goulash.
Spread Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese in between 3 layers.
Cover top with Ricotta and Mozzarella cheeses.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: debbie's party spread
directions: Mix and refrigerate the day before serving. I just use one whole jar of pimientos and drain them on a paper
towel.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook the lasagne noodles in boiling water until tender; drain. (Use 8 lasagne noodles for 2 layers of noodles.) Brown the ground beef, then drain. Add the spaghetti sauces to ground beef; simmer for a few minutes. Put small amount of beef-sauce mixture in the bottom of large cake pan or oblong casserole dish. Put a layer of noodles, 1/2 sauce mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle Parmesan cheese. Repeat and cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg yolks until fluffy.
Mix salt and soda in flour.
Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: mustard pickles relish
directions: Cut cucumbers, tomatoes and onions thin.
Add cauliflower, salt and water.
Add vinegar, sugar, flour, dry mustard and turmeric; bring to a boil.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Combine yogurt and mustard, stirring until well blended. Brush breast halves evenly with yogurt mixture and dredge in bread crumbs.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all in blender eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla, salt, Bisquick and shortening.
Beat alone for 2 minutes in blender.
Add coconut and blend by hand.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tacos
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan.
Add pink beans and mash them while cooking.
Add taco seasoning mix and 1/2 to 3/4 cup water. Cook about 15 minutes on low.
Chop up vegetables.
When cooked, fill taco shells or roll in soft tortillas.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes or heat in microwave until warm.
Garnish with chopped vegetables, cheese, salsa and sour cream.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine pineapple juice, pudding mix and Tang breakfast drink. Set aside. In a large bowl, combine all the fruit. Fold juice mixture into fruit. Refrigerate before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli braid
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Chop chicken, broccoli and pepper and place in a medium bowl.
Sprinkle with garlic powder over vegetable mixture.
Add cheese, dill weed, mayonnaise and salt and mix gently.
Unroll dinner rolls, do not separate, and arrange on a cookie sheet one beside the other to form about 12 x 15 inch dough.
Seal all of the perforations.
From the 12 inch side, cut 1 1/2 inch strips on each side about 3 inches long so there is about 6 inches not cut.
Spread filling evenly down the center of the dough.
Lift one of the strips from each side and take to center, then a strip from the other side to the center and so on, alternating to form a braid.
At the end, tuck the ends under to seal the end of the braid.
Brush egg whites over the dough and bake 25 to 28 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in greased muffin pan.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli until crisp-tender.
Chop.
Combine broccoli, broth and onion and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Puree mixture in blender until smooth.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: In a small bowl, mix the flour and baking soda.
Set aside. In a big bowl, add the margarine, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and pudding.
After creaming these ingredients, add the eggs until batter is creamy again.
Gradually add flour mixture.
(If batter is thick, add 1 to 2 tablespoons water.)
Mix in the chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Set aside.
Cut cheese into cubes and melt in microwave.
Add garlic powder to cheese and stir until well blended.
Add sausage to cheese mixture and stir until well blended.
Spread on pumpernickel bread and lay flat on baking sheet.
Place under broiler until lightly browned.
Watch closely as it only takes a couple of minutes to brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into small balls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°; bake 15 minutes longer.

title: batter bread
directions: Place milk in large mixer bowl.
Add sugar and sprinkle yeast over surface.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add salt, lightly beaten eggs and soft butter.
Little by little add half of the flour and mix at a slow speed.
Add remainder of the flour and continue beating until the batter shreds from the mixer beaters.
Place the batter in a greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down the dough.
Beat with a spatula for a few minutes and turn into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Let rise again until almost double in bulk.
Brush with Egg Yolk Glaze.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: dipsy devil dip
directions: In 2-quart dish, put cheese. Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Serve with raw vegetables such as cauliflower, carrots, cucumbers or bell peppers. Serves 10.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients. Lightly put mixture in greased loaf pan.
Smooth top.
May sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: carrot-pineapple cupcakes(makes 8 cupcakes)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place paper baking cups in muffin tins. Mix dry ingredients thoroughly in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Fill baking cups two-thirds full.
Bake 20 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Bring milk to boiling point (can be heated in microwave).
Add sugar and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Add to softened butter and approximately 2 tablespoons of shortening.
Mix at high speed.
If curdling, add more shortening.
Add vanilla and almond.

title: date roll
directions: Mix ingredients together and form a roll.
(I use wax paper to form an oblong roll and/or put in a bread wrapper to keep from drying out.)
Set in refrigerator overnight or 2 nights in a cool place.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Beat sugar and butter together, then add eggs.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Add flour; blend well.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Pour into a greased pie plate.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: delicious mexican layer dip
directions: Brown ground beef, add seasoning mix as directed and simmer 10 minutes.
When meat cools, use as bottom layer in pan/dish. Spread salsa on top of meat.
Sprinkle with half of cheese. Add green olives.
Spread with sour cream, layer of ripe olives and green chilies.
Top with rest of cheese.
Serve with 2 (10 ounce) bags of your favorite tortilla chips.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix Italian dressing and water.
Bring to a boil; add rice. Set aside.
Let cool.
Mix English peas, water chestnuts, chopped mushrooms and chopped cucumber.
Add cooked rice and mayonnaise. Mix well.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until done.
Remove chicken and add water to make at least 3 quarts of broth.
Add potatoes, corn and onion; cook until done.
Add eggs, chopped chicken and parsley.
Bring to a boil and serve.

title: homemade sauerkraut
directions: Combine cabbage and salt in large bowl; stir well.
Pack solidly into pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Fill with water, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw bands tight.
Allow to ferment at room temperature for 3 to 4 days. (Small amount of liquid will escape jars.)
Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.

title: the best family pie
directions: This is the beginning of a new day.

title: butterfingers
directions: Boil to 300° the sugar, water and syrup.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour into a buttered 10 x 15-inch pan. Cut while warm in bars.
Let cool and dip in chocolate.
Please note, cheap peanut butter works best as it seems to contain more oil.
You must stir the peanut butter in as fast as you can.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk. Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour half of the mixture over graham crackers, then place second layer of grahams over pudding mixture. Pour remaining pudding mixture over grahams and cover with more crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours, then frost.

title: raisin-rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except nutmeg in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix thoroughly.
Place casserole in pan filled 1 inch deep with hot water.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway comes out clean.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Serve warm or cold.

title: rhubarb pudding cake
directions: Cook rhubarb, 1 cup sugar and water until tender.
Keep hot. Cream shortening and 1/2 cup sugar; beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Spoon hot rhubarb sauce over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Open 1 can of fruit cocktail.
Add peeled oranges.
Remove all thick hull.
Cut up fine.
Peel apples and pears.
Cut up.
Add to fruit cocktail.
Stir in few grapes.
Mix well in bowl.
Top with coconut.
Chill.
Serve with cake or eat as a fruit cup.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender, then drain.
Mix together the mayonnaise, mustard and pickles; pour over potatoes.
Dice egg; add to mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
More or less mayonnaise can be used, if you wish.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Wash and slice zucchini into 1/4-inch slices. Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven (or a slow cooker) and let simmer at least 1 hour.
Add a little water if you cook much longer.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in pan, then put cherries on top.
Sprinkle cake mix and nuts over top.
Cut up stick of oleo on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: molded spinach salad
directions: Thaw spinach under running hot water.
I use 4 small packages for about 6 servings.
Drain spinach well, squeezing out water. Lightly grease muffin tins with mayonnaise and pack spinach into each one.
Cover and chill until firm.

title: portuguese tuna custard pie
directions: Bake pastry shell in preheated 425° oven about 5 minutes, until set but not brown.
Beat together the eggs, cream, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Stir in tuna, Swiss cheese and chives.
Turn into partially baked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or until tip of knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.
Serve with tomato sauce, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet icicle pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers in quarters lengthwise; put in stone jar or stainless steel container.
Add salt to water and bring to a boil. Pour over cucumbers.
Cover with plate to keep cucumbers under brine.
Let stand for 1 week in cool place.
Drain and rinse cucumbers thoroughly.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 24 hours.
Drain and add alum to cucumbers; cover with boiling water. Let stand 24 hours; drain.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Top with additional grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, sugar, grated orange zest, spices, salt, pumpkin and orange juice.
Beat with electric mixer until mixture is smooth (no lumps remaining). Pour into an unbaked pie crust and bake for 55 minutes or until filling is set in center.
Cool on wire rack.
Just before serving, circle perimeter with whipped cream, then across the center.
Garnish with shredded orange zest.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Blend; beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut, nuts and chocolate.
Pour into greased, floured 11-cup ring mold or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: one pot supper
directions: In skillet, brown chops; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir frequently.

title: taramasalata, fish roe dipgreece
directions: Mash the Tarama and add the grated onion. Add a little of the olive oil and beat thoroughly to a smooth paste.
Moisten the bread and squeeze out the excess water.
Continue beating Tarama mixture, adding alternately small bits of moistened bread, olive oil and lemon juice.
Taramasalata should be beaten until cream colored. Serve as a dip with crackers or spread on toast. Makes 1 1/2-2 cups.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Assemble and attach Slicer/Shredder, using Fine Shredder Cone (No. 1).
Turn to Speed 4 and shred zucchini.
Set aside.
Replace Fine Shredder with Coarse Shredder Cone (No. 2).
Turn to Speed 4 and chop nuts into separate bowl.
Attach Bowl and Beater and add eggs.
Turn to Speed 4 and beat until eggs are light and foamy, about 2 minutes.
Stop.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla. Turn to Stir Speed and mix until well blended, about 1 minute. Stop.

title: crispy pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Pour into greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Put pan of water in oven while cake bakes.

title: carrots and apples
directions: In medium saucepan of boiling water, cook carrots for 8 to 10 minutes; drain.

title: unbelievable cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Have ingredients at room temperature. Blend all ingredients, except cottage cheese and cinnamon, thoroughly in blender. Gradually add cottage cheese. Blend until smooth. Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Top with cinnamon. Bake 45 minutes or until cake is firm. Turn off oven and leave the cheese cake there with the door open for 1 hour. Serves 6. Contains 199 calories per serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper; drain. Add other ingredients to meat in a 2-quart casserole. Stir well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: First, soak Junket tablets in water.
Beat eggs.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Add milk and and cream.
Heat this to lukewarm and add dissolved Junket tablets.
Stir and put in freezer to set. Let set at least 15 minutes.
Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients in the order given; mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake in a hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°; continue baking for 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over
All-Bran; let stand until cool.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt (put aside).
Cream sugar, honey and shortening.
Add eggs.
Blend in buttermilk, Grape-Nuts and All-Bran mixture.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Store in gallon jar in refrigerator.
It will keep up to 6 weeks.

title: grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine grits, milk, butter, egg yolks and salt.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into grits mixture.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: cookie salad
directions: Break up package of cookies into small pieces.
Set aside.

title: stromboli
directions: Cook meats. Drain. Add pizza sauce, water, Parmesan, garlic powder and oregano. Spread soft margarine on buns.
Add meat. Sprinkle top of meat with lots of Mozzarella.
Warm in oven until cheese is melted.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine flour, egg, shortening, salt and water; mix well to form soft dough.
Roll out paper thin; let dry for 20 minutes. Cut in small strips; drop in boiling broth.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add egg.
Stir lightly and serve.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Grease and flour a 10 inch tube pan. Combine the butter and cream cheese in a large mixing bowl. Beat until well blended. Add the sugar and beat until smooth and creamy. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
This is an important step because the eggs provide the leavening for this cake. Add the flour alternately with the milk, starting and ending with the flour.

Stir in the mini-chips. Pour into the prepared pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake. Remove from the pan immediately and turn upright onto a serving plate. Allow to cool before slicing.

title: cream-style corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add the 2 cans of corn.
In a separate dish, beat egg.
Add milk and flour to egg; mix well. Add salt and pepper to egg mixture.
Pour egg mixture over corn in casserole dish.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gak
directions: Dissolve Borax in 1/4 cup water in a paper or plastic cup.
In another cup, mix 1/8 cup Elmer's glue with 1/8 cup water.
Stir well.
Add food coloring, if desired, to the glue mixture and stir.
Pour the Borax solution
into the glue mixture and stir. Drain the extra liquid down the sink.
Be careful not to lose the slime.
Knead in your hands until it firms like putty, then store in a sealable plastic bag in the refrigerator.
Do not eat!

title: no bake oatmeal candy
directions: Heat
first
4	ingredients over low heat.
Add vanilla until mixture
comes to barely bubbling.	Pour in oatmeal and add peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: oriental sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in small bowl.
Sprinkle with finely chopped green onion, if desired.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: molasses krinkles
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shape into balls. Dip top in sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hearty soup
directions: Brown bacon and sausage in Dutch oven.
Add onion and celery and saute 5 minutes.
Add beef broth.
Add kidney beans, cooked spaghetti and canned tomatoes.
Simmer until flavor is well blended, about 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients with exception of sugar.
Add oil and vanilla to dry ingredients and beat until it forms a very smooth batter.
In separate bowl, beat eggs until thick and foamy. Gradually add sugar and continue beating until well blended.
Fold egg and sugar mixture thoroughly into flour batter.
Add pecans and apples.
Bake in Bundt pan in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: elva's chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, stirring in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Frost with Butter Cream Frosting or leave plain.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: *May substitute scallops for shrimp.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Spread mix on tortilla shells. Roll like jelly roll and wrap in Saran Wrap. Chill, slice and serve with salsa.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs together.
Add carrots.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add alternately to batter with oil.
Add nuts and pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in skillet and saute onion until golden.
Add broccoli, beaten eggs and rest of ingredients except fillo.
Butter the inside of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Place in one fillo leaf and butter it.
Do the same with four more leaves.
Dump in the filling.
Cover the top with the part of the leaves that hang over.
Cut 5 (9-inch) fillo circles.
Place one at a time on top, buttering each layer.
Score the top of the pie. Pour remaining butter over the top.
Place on a cookie sheet to catch the drippings.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until puffy and golden.
Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems up fine and brown in butter.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing and add stems to mixture. Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and put filled mushrooms in pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: confetti biscuit ring
directions: Quarter biscuits and place in large bowl.
Coat biscuits with the butter.
Add rest of ingredients to the biscuit mixture and toss lightly.
Pat into lightly greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave tomato citrus soup
directions: Combine tomato soup, orange juice, chicken broth, lemon juice and sugar in 4 cup glass measure.
Cook on High for 5 to 5 1/2 minutes or until hot.
Serve with croutons, Parmesan cheese or a dollop of sour cream.

title: fruit filled coffee cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat and blend well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder. Blend together well.
Pour half the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over this pour the can of pie filling.
Pour remaining mixture on top.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Mix crumbs and cheese. Roll chicken in mixture until coated.
Melt margarine in skillet (about 4 tablespoons).
Brown chicken on both sides.
(I use a lid while browning.)
Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Add wine.
Pour over chicken.
Simmer until all liquid is cooked out.
Sprinkle any leftover crumb mixture over chicken before browning.

title: her majesty cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together, add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 (8-inch) layers.

title: chicken salad tarts
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening and margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle milk (one tablespoon at a time) evenly over surface.
Stir with a fork just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: appetizer pronto
directions: Pour salsa over Neufchatel cheese; top with Cheddar cheese. Serve with crackers or party rye bread slices.

title: moist rolled oat cake
directions: Mix together and let stand 15 minutes the boiling water and oatmeal.

title: chocolate chip cookie dough
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli (undercook).
Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese, bread crumbs and melted butter.
Pour mixture over chicken and sprinkle with the cheese.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mock chocolate eclairs
directions: Place whole graham crackers on the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip until thick.
Spread over graham crackers.
Layer whole graham crackers on top.
Cover with frosting.
Let stand in refrigerator 12 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 10 minutes; drain well.
Add mayonnaise, chopped onion, cream of mushroom soup and eggs.
Mix well; pour into Pyrex dish.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and mix with Cheddar cheese and stuffing mix.
Put on top of broccoli mixture and cover with foil. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
This can be prepared the night before and refrigerated.

title: ginger lace cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Make into small balls and roll in sugar.
Do not press down and leave room on cookie sheets to spread.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: southern egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. In large bowl, beat eggs slightly, using a fork. Add the sugar and melted margarine. Stir until well mixed. Gradually add the milk, stirring well. Line a metal strainer with a double thickness of cheesecloth. Strain the custard through the cheesecloth into the pie crust. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until a thin knife blade comes out clean when inserted into the custard halfway between the edge of the pan and the center of the custard. Remove to a rack and cool completely before slicing. Refrigerate after completely cooled.

title: chicken curry
directions: Brown curry powder with melted butter for 1 minute. Add apple and onion.
Brown for 2 minutes. Add cream of mushroom soup and cream. Remove from heat.
Arrange chicken in single layer in a baking dish. Salt and paprika well. Pour cream mixture over chicken. Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients
together.
Add vinegar, oil, vanilla and water.
Mix well.
Lightly spray a jelly roll pan with Pam. Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with your favorite icing.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring to boil sugar and syrup.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter.
Stirring until dissolved.
Add 6 cups cereal.
Mix thoroughly.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pat with fingers to pack down.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together and pour on top of cereal mixture.
Takes several hours to harden.
Cut into small squares.
Keeps fresh a long time and freezes very well (48 or more pieces).

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Heat and mix together the soup and Cheez Whiz.
Combine all ingredients, except onion rings.
Pour into casserole dish; top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: clark bars
directions: Mix margarine, oatmeal, brown sugar, sugar, vanilla and salt and press in pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, then cool. Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together and spread on top, then cool.

title: "feta psomakia" - feta rolls
directions: Cut crust off of bread and roll bread with rolling pin.
Brush on butter.
Combine Feta cheese and cream cheese (you may use sour cream) also and spread on rolled bread slice.
Roll up and dip into egg dip.
Then roll in sesame seed or poppy seed.
Broil until crust forms.
Slice.
Or slice before broiling.
Sides are crisp, too.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Steam broccoli for 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: brown sugar fudge cake
directions: Cream butter. Sift flour, soda and salt into butter. Add sugar, 2/3 cup buttermilk and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes. Add remaining buttermilk, eggs and cooled chocolate. Beat 2 minutes. Pour mixture into two 9-inch layer pans lined on bottom with paper. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: a special recipe for a happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and add tears of joy and sorrow and sympathy for others.
Flavor with little gifts of love and kindly service.
Fold in 4 cups of prayers and bake it with a smile.
Cut a small piece every morning and be happy.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix above ingredients together. Top with shredded cheese or cornflakes. Bake in 9 x 13 pan for 75 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut deboned chicken into small pieces.
Mix soup, sour cream and poppy seed.
Put chicken in casserole dish.
Pour sour cream mixture on top.
Melt butter and add butter to Ritz crackers.
Mix well.
Put on top of casserole.
Cook at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: shawn's chili(prep time: 2 hours)
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and green peppers.
Combine all ingredients in 3 to 4-quart saucepan and simmer on stove for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until beans are hot.
Serve as a chili spread for chili dogs or on crisp tostadas, filler for burritos and just plain chili.
This tastes even better the next day!!

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix the cake mix, eggs and oil well in a medium-sized bowl. Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Space about 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool before serving.

title: chocolate coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and sugar. Heat butter, Coca-Cola and cocoa over medium heat to boiling point. Pour over flour mixture and stir. Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows. Batter will be thin. Bake in well greased 3-quart dish for 35 minutes.

title: suzy's pear cobbler
directions: Mix sugar with cornstarch.
Add to pears in pan.
Add other ingredients and simmer to mix.
While you do this, cut pie crust in strips.
Spray Pam in your glass dish.
Lay strips of one crust and sprinkle sugar, butter and cinnamon over.
Cook at 400° until golden.
Take from oven and add pear mix to this; it will sizzle. Put strips from other crust over the pears.
Dot with butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Cook at 400° for 25 minutes.
Use oblong glass dish (large one).
Also can use peaches or berries.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar; spread in 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cream Cool Whip and cream cheese together and spread on pretzel mixture.
Mix jello, hot water and strawberries; let set until slightly thickened, then spread on Cool Whip and cream cheese layer.
Do not let jello completely set.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1/2 stick butter (melted) and corn flakes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Take out and put other 1/2 stick of melted butter and corn flakes on top.
Put back in oven for 15 minutes.

title: pickle stix
directions: Cut cucumbers into sticks.
Cover with water and soak for 4 or 5 hours.
Drain.
Pack in jars.
Combine all other ingredients. Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers in jars.
Process boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: jellied apple nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water, lemon juice and salt.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients except greens.
Pour into 1-quart mold or an 8 x 8-inch pan, 2 inches thick.
Chill until firm.
Calories per serving:
about 105.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Grease the bottom of pan.
Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add all ingredients except eggs. Stir to mix.
Add eggs and beat well.
Bake in 2 x 8 x 8-inch square pan or one with similar surface area about 12 x 12-inch or 10 x 14-inch for about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
All preparation may be done in saucepan.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 32 brownies.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, melt the margarine over moderate heat; slice the onion and add to saucepan, cooking, uncovered, until golden, 8 to 10 minutes.
Blend the sugar and flour; cook, stirring, 3 minutes longer.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cook with Pam or small amount of oil in skillet.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Let cook for about 5 minutes.
Add stir-fry sauce, water and dash of Tabasco sauce.
Simmer about 5 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Cake - In a large mixer bowl beat eggs with an electric mixer on high speed
for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in the granulated sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
In a small bowl, stir together the flour, cinnamon, baking powder, ginger, salt and nutmeg.
Fold into the pumpkin mixture.
Spread the batter into a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1 inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Immediately invert the cake onto a towel which has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll
up the cake and towel jelly-roll style, starting from one of the short sides. Cool completely and unroll the cake.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Cook all ingredients, except bacon, over low heat for 10 or 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf; sprinkle with crisp bacon.

title: tri-berry muffins(from open house cookbook by sara leah chase)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Put paper liners in 24 muffin cups. Stir the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture.
Add the milk, eggs and butter (melted) to the well. Stir quickly just to combine. Add the berries and sugar.
Stir quickly again just to combine.

title: easy-mix chocolate drop cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given, except nuts.
Beat at medium speed for 4 to 5 minutes; add nuts.
Drop on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, frost tops with fudge frosting if desired.
Yield:
3 to 4 dozen.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with whisk until smooth. Gently stir in 1/2 of the Cool Whip. Spread on bottom of crust. Pour 1 cup milk into bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 1 minute. (Mixture will be thick.) Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk until well mixed. Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish with remaining Cool Whip. Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: tabouli
directions: Wash parsley & chop fine.
In bowl, cover burghul with warm water to soak for 10 mins. Water will be absorbed.
Combine parsley, soft, drained burghul and remainder of ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk and mix in with crushed Honey Grahams.
Mix in nuts, raisins and fruit; mix well.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Heat and mix shortening and milk; stir until melted.
Add sugar, salt and cold water.
Add eggs after taking off stove.
Mix well.
Add yeast and 1/2 of the flour and beat until well mixed. Add rest of flour.
Place in bowl and let it rise.
Place in oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until brown.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Divide cauliflower into small pieces along with lettuce. Chop onions. Toss above ingredients in large bowl. Add bacon bits just before serving.

title: austrian chocolate mousse
directions: Place chocolate bits and unsweetened chocolate, broken into pieces, in a bowl.
Pour boiling water over chocolate to cover. Cover bowl tightly and let stand 5 minutes.
Uncover, and carefully pour off as much water as possible.
Add confectioners sugar, vanilla, egg yolks and butter.
Beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into mixture and pour into a pretty glass or china serving dish.
Chill for several hours or until set. Serves 6.

title: fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a tube pan, line with wax paper and grease again or use a generously greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, confectioners sugar, peanut butter and melted margarine together.
Pat solid in 8 x 8-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon margarine.
Spread over top.
Cut into small squares when cool.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour, sugar, salt and Crisco together. Beat together vinegar, cold water and egg. Combine liquids with flour-Crisco mixture.
Makes 4 pie crusts.
May freeze.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add milk and flour sifted with soda, baking powder and spices.
Add dates and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet in 375° oven.
At Christmas, decorate with candied cherry and colored sugar before baking.

title: micro white sauce
directions: Pour milk into 2 cup glass measure. Use Cook cycle and cook 2 minutes; set aside. Place butter in 2 cup glass measure. Use Cook cycle and cook 1 minute or until melted.

Stir in flour. Use Cook cycle and cook 1 minute. Briskly stir in warm milk, pepper and nutmeg. Use Cook cycle and cook 4 1/2 to 5 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring once during cooking time. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Total cooking time is 8 1/2 to 9 minutes.

title: no-bakes
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cook until it bubbles, then about 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or pan. Let cool.

title: lobster salad
directions: In top of a double boiler melt cream cheese and mayonnaise; add the dissolved gelatin.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serve on lettuce.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate 6 to 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: stripe it rich cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Remove baked cake from oven; immediately poke holes in cake 1 inch apart, using wooden spoon handle.
Only after poking holes, combine instant pudding, powdered sugar and milk.
Beat at low speed for not more than 1 minute; do not overbeat.
Quickly, before pudding thickens, pour 1/2 of the thin pudding evenly over warm cake into holes to make stripes.
Allow remaining pudding to thicken slightly, then spoon over the top, swirling it to frost the cake.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: *wheatie macaroons
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugars gradually and cream well.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix together.
Add coconut and the dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Add Wheaties and nuts last.
Fold into batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for about 10 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken) in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn and bake on other side for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Luscious! Delicious!
Easy!

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle cake mix over mixture.
Drizzle one stick melted margarine over top.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
(It is better to bake day before serving.)
Refrigerate. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Heat sugar, corn syrup and water.
Stir until sugar dissolves. When syrup mixture boils, blend in margarine.
Stir frequently. Add peanuts when mixture becomes 280°.
Stir constantly until it reaches the cracking stage (305°).
Remove from heat quickly; stir in baking soda.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Pour sugar over fruit.
Sprinkle with flour and dot with butter.
Set aside fruit mixture.
In large bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour batter over fruit, leaving space in the middle and around the edges.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: slushy fruity punch
directions: Mix sugar and water in a gallon container.
Add prepared lemonade and orange juice.
Blend in crushed pineapple and juice, bananas, cherries, peaches and strawberries.
Blend all ingredients well; freeze.
Take out needed portion in a glass and add ginger ale.
Stir until slushy and enjoy.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add other ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Mash flat with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: people chow
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Stir in cereal.
Put sugar in paper bag and add chocolate-coated cereal. Shake until well coated.

title: sugar cookies(bake off recipe)
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add the Crisco and flake like a pie crust.
Add the eggs, sour cream and vanilla all at one time. Combine all. Roll each cookie individually in flour and sugar.
Fork and sprinkle with sugar, etc. Bake 10 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes about 120 cookies.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Add taco seasoning and beans, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken wings.
Lightly salt and pepper and fry in oil.
Do not use a batter.
Set aside to drain.
In a separate skillet, melt 3 tablespoons of butter and add hot sauce and vinegar.
Place 6 to 8 cooked wings in a skillet and thoroughly coat each wing.
Set aside in ovenproof dish and keep warm in low oven.
Repeat process until all wings have been coated with sauce. The sauce doubles well for time saving.
Serve with celery sticks and Blue Cheese Dressing.
The Blue Cheese Dressing will cut the hot sauce.

title: lazy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Roll out bread dough on floured pastry sheet to form a 14-inch circle.
Defrost broccoli and chop, if using spears.
