Lay Provolone cheese on dough, next add pepperoni slices, Mozzarella cheese, broccoli, Colby and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bring sides and ends of the pastry up to the top and pinch to seal.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
This bread can be used as an appetizer or as a main dish served with a fresh garden salad.

title: cream cheese pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together until well blended.
Add egg and mix well.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Mix together pumpkin, sugar, spices and salt.
Add evaporated milk and eggs.
Mix well and pour over cream cheese layer of pie.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
After pie cools, cover with a thin layer of maple syrup and decorate with pecan halves if desired.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix bread cubes, margarine, onion and seasonings.
Cut pockets in pork chops.
Stuff with dressing.
Wrap cord string around chops to hold dressing.
Arrange in roasting pan, leaving cover off and brown in hot oven.
Mix water, catsup and Worcestershire sauce; pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until tender.

title: shrimp and broccoli linguine
directions: Cook linguine using package directions.
Keep warm.
Saute garlic in butter in skillet.
Add olive oil.
Heat for 30 seconds. Add broccoli and stir-fry for several minutes.
Add shrimp and stir-fry for 2 minutes or until heated through.
Serve over hot linguine.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: sweet-n-sour sauce
directions: Mix both together until desired taste.
The amount of each ingredient is up to your taste.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes.
Blend powdered sugar, butter and egg until of spreading consistency.
Spread over crust. Cut bananas on top lengthwise.
Top with pineapple, then Cool Whip, cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust that has been shaped to fit the pan.
Top with pie crust.
Cut slits to let out steam.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: rice and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except paprika and place in an oiled 2-quart casserole.
Dust top with paprika and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cooked lettuce
directions: Make a mixture of vinegar, sugar and water to a sweet and sour taste.
(Use very little water because so much cooks out of lettuce.)
Just use enough so it won't burn.
Pour over lettuce and cook until completely wilted.
Takes a good while.

title: frozen cheesecake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with cracker crumbs.
Beat yolks, sugar and cheese mixture until smooth. Combine with whites and pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend well the cheese and oleo.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika.
Mix well. Wrap approximately 1 teaspoon cheese dough around each olive.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, store in covered container until ready to cook.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove desired amount and bake for 15 minutes.

title: walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add white Karo syrup and 2 to 3 cups walnuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
This makes 2 pies.
Pecans can be substituted for walnuts to make a pecan pie.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, salt, Karo and butter to 200° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add baking soda (will get foamy). Pour popcorn on baking sheets and pour caramel mixture over corn. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in a bowl of melted butter, then dip into a bowl of a mixture of Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs and parsley.
After which, place chicken parts on a baking sheet ready to bake.

title: chili macaroni
directions: Cook beef, onion and celery until beef is well browned.
Drain; break up large pieces of tomatoes.
Add remaining ingredients to meat mixture.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and boil gently until mixture is thickened and macaroni is tender; about 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings (1 1/4 cups) each.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend together ingredients, except cheese and potato chips. Drop into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese, then potato chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until cheese is melted and delicately browned and bubbly.

title: chili
directions: Combine kidney beans, whole tomatoes and tomato sauce into a crock-pot.
Fry onions, mushrooms, green and red pepper.
When cooked, add to crock-pot.
Fry ground beef; drain and add to crock-pot.
Add chili powder and garlic to taste.
Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Mix
shortening
and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and M&M's.
Put teaspoonful of batter onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut broccoli and put in casserole dish.
Add sauteed onion and mushrooms on top of broccoli.
Add 2 cans cream of mushroom soup (do not add water).
Add stuffing.
Top with American cheese, sliced.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into sprayed casserole dish. Cover with topping.

title: spring garden soup
directions: In saucepan in 1 cup water, cook peas, potatoes and onions until tender.
In a bowl or another pan, combine boiling water, bouillon cubes, celery salt and curry powder.
In a blender, puree undrained cooked vegetables until smooth.
Blend into bouillon.

title: hot tortellini
directions: Boil the tortellini for 8 minutes.
Melt 1 stick butter and saute mushrooms and spinach.
Sprinkle with garlic powder to taste.
Melt 1 sticks butter and 2 cheeses. Add milk and cook until creamy. Drain tortellini and mix everything together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm.

title: butter pecan turtle squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, 1 cup brown sugar and 4 ounces butter in mixing bowl.
Mix until sandy.
The dough will not form a ball.
Pat dough firmly into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans over dough.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Constantly stir until thick.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to a boil. Add Jell-O and pour over sliced strawberries in a baked crust. When cool, add whipped topping.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: salmon fillets
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Place salmon fillets over onion in skillet.
Pour on soy sauce.
Cover and simmer over medium-low heat until salmon is just opaque in center, 10 to 12 minutes.
Transfer the salmon to platter.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend sugar, pumpkin, Crisco and eggs. Add flour, baking powder and spices. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture; stir in nuts, raisins or dates.
Pour into greased (do not flour) loaf pans.
Coffee cans may be used also.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.

title: mcfarlane's mexican dip
directions: In 8 or 9-inch pie plate, spread cream cheese over bottom. Cover cream cheese completely with chili.
Grate cheese over top of chili.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: nellie's salsa
directions: Clean and roast peppers on all sides equally.
After roasting them, wrap in towel and let set 20 minutes.
Cut end off and peel the peppers.
Cut in long, thin strips and then cut crossways. Leave seed in.
Peel tomatoes and smash them in peppers.
If more sauce is needed, add 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Season with salt and garlic.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar in a pan with vinegar, being careful not to let it burn.
When melted, add peanuts, stirring as little as possible. Pour on a buttered platter.
Break up when cold.

title: charlie's famous salmon salad
directions: Steam fillets. Remove skin and bones from salmon and then flake. Combine remainder of the ingredients with the flaked salmon.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cook cake as directed.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground round and drain grease from meat.
Add taco sauce, ketchup and mustard.
Makes 4 large or 6 small Sloppy Joes.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Melt chocolate.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, then melted chocolate.
Add vanilla, salt, nuts and optional flavoring.
Pour in pan on aluminum foil; cool and cut.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Spray 9 x 13 inch pan with Pam.
Roll the quartered apples in the crescent rolls.
Place apples in pan.
Mix melted butter, cinnamon and sugar and pour over apples and crescents.
Add Mountain Dew along the edges for additional secret flavor.
Bake 45 minutes - 1 hour at 350 degrees or until the apples are soft.

title: toby's famous onion rings
directions: Cut onion into rings.
Mix water with the pancake mix (about 3/4 to 1 cup water).
Mixture should coat rings thinly.
Fry in medium-hot grease until golden brown.
Salt to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain water.
Cook Pet cream and Cheez Whiz together, stirring constantly.
Melt 2 sticks of butter and crumble 2 packages of crackers in butter.
Cover broccoli and Cheez Whiz with butter cracker topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy nut triangles
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add egg yolk only and vanilla.
Add flour and cinnamon. Mix well. Dough will be thick.
Spread in greased and floured pan (15 x 10-inch).
Beat egg white with fork, pour over dough.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: egg kisses
directions: Use mixer.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually. Add cream of tartar, salt and vanilla.
Mix until stiff.
Bake at about 250° for 1 hour or longer.

title: beefy goodness
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until almost done; drain fat.
Add steak and brown slowly.
Add bouillon mixture, mustard and onion.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and cold water.
Add to skillet and heat until thick.
Remove from skillet and add sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheddar cheese
directions: Empty soup into 2-quart casserole.
Stir in milk gradually. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 20 to 35 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Let stand covered 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: low-fat pumpkin bread
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature.
Put all ingredients into the bread machine in the order listed.
Select white bread and push "Start".

title: peaches 'n cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix. Coat 9-inch pan with Pam.
Pour batter into pan.
Place peaches over batter.
In separate bowl, cream together cheese, peach juice and sugar.
Spread over peaches to cover peaches completely.
Cook for 35 minutes.
Cool at least 45 minutes before serving.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream eggs and sugar.
Add flour with soda and cocoa.
Add
to eggs and sugar along with Wesson oil. Blend in buttermilk, vanilla and vinegar.
Then add food coloring. Pour into greased
and
floured cake pans.
Makes 3 layers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Mix in egg and flavoring.
Stir dry ingredients together; blend into sugar mixture.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Roll dough to 3/16-inch thickness.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
May be decorated with your favorite icing.

title: crunchy crust for peaches
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and egg.
Spoon on top of slightly sweetened peaches that have been put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: brown sugar coffee cake(breakfast)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Then add egg yolks.
Add grated lemon rind and beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Place half of batter in greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Prepare Topping.

title: dave's gusty gumbo
directions: Thaw fish and shrimp.
Remove skin from fish and devein the shrimp.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Rinse, then chill in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: microwave hot cocoa
directions: Mix sugar, cold water and cocoa in medium mixing bowl. Microwave at High (100%) until thickened, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.
Blend in milk.
Microwave on High until hot, 4 to 6 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Serves 4.

title: poor man's fruit cake
directions: Gently simmer for 20 minutes the raisins, dates, sugar, water and shortening.
Cool.
Sift together and stir in dry ingredients. Mix in nuts.
Pour into two well-greased and floured loaf pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 3/4 hours.

title: sour cream or yogurt dressing
directions: For Fruit Salads:
Blend sour cream and fruit juice.

title: chess pie
directions: Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 40 minutes or so at 300°.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of cookie sheet with crescent rolls, pressed together to form crust.
Bake crust at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes. Cool.
Mix Miracle Whip, cream cheese and dressing mix.
Spread evenly on crust.
Cover with finely chopped vegetables and cheese. Press vegetables into cream cheese mixture with paper towels to remove moisture.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherry pie filling.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost when cool (recipe follows).

title: chocolate amaretto truffles
directions: Melt chocolate with Amaretto and Espresso in top of double boiler over simmering water.
Stir until smooth.
Remove top from double boiler from heat.
Whisk in butter 1 tablespoon at a time until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours.
Scoop mixture into rough round shapes.
Roll in cocoa and place in paper cups.
Store in refrigerator up to 3 days.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in hot water and let stand until thawed, then drain.
Melt oleo in the baking dish in oven.
Mix everything together and put in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake in greased baking dish 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Cook over low heat until melted.
Combine cake mix, soft margarine and rest of evaporated milk.
Mix until crumbly.
Press 3/4 of mix in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Pour melted caramels, nuts and chocolate chips on top.
Crumble remaining cake mix on top.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift
flour; add baking powder, sugar and salt and sift again. Core apples.
Cut in slices crosswise.
Dip each slice of apple in	the batter and fry in deep, hot fat until brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Heat fat to 370° to 375°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine
chicken, celery, grapes, salt and pepper.
Add mayonnaise and
sour cream; mix well.
Put in glass bowl lined with lettuce leaves.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Chill.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling in 9 x 13 pan. Cut edges off bread, cover pie filling. Mix remaining ingredients; pour over bread. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: tina's stir-fry
directions: Brown meat in a large frypan.
Remove from pan.
Stir-fry vegetables in a small amount of oil until tender. Add meat.
Add wine to taste or extra Worcestershire sauce. Serve over rice.

title: crown cake
directions: *Add a small amount of almond or lemon for difference.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and sift again.
Cream sugar, Crisco and oleo.
Add eggs (one at a time), beating well after each one.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Add flour gradually, beating well.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Divide batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is firm.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Pour melted butter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer other ingredients in order. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool before cutting into squares.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix the remaining ingredients together; spread over cooled baked mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: facial cleansing cream
directions: Fluff in a mixing bowl.
Store in opaque jars.
You can't buy a better cleansing cream, at any price.
Recommended by two nurses. 1930's recipe.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked crust and bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: mocha angel cake
directions: Mix cocoa into dry cake mix.
Substitute cold coffee for water called for on mix.
Follow baking directions on box.
Cool. Frost with mocha frosting.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion.
Add potato and cover with water. Bring to a boil.
Add corn and simmer.
Add cream, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Ready to serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, sift flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, cloves, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Make a hole in dry ingredients.
Pour in cooking oil, pumpkin and water; blend well together.
Add eggs.
Pour into 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant italiano
directions: Make like you would for spaghetti or lasagna.
Grease casserole dish.
Now alternate layers of sauce (blend cottage cheese, eggs and oregano until smooth), eggplant and cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato cheese scallopel paso, texas
directions: Slice potatoes into baking dish.
Combine sour cream, eggs, milk, onion and salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover with cheese.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll dough into medium size balls (smaller than golf ball size).
Roll balls in melted butter, then in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Starting with nuts, alternate layers of nuts and sugared balls into greased Bundt pan.
Pour remaining butter and sugar-cinnamon over all.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert immediately onto plate after baking.

title: ground beef with green chili quiche
directions: Bake piecrust in 450 degree oven for 5 minutes or until crust starts to brown. Brown ground beef and onion. Add seasonings and chilies. Pour mixture into piecrust. Top with cheese. Bake at 350 degrees until brown or cheese is melted.

title: browned rice and pork
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim fat from chops; sprinkle with salt (seasoned salt).
Brown chops well on both sides in skillet. Place in 2-quart casserole.
Add rice to drippings in skillet and cook until rice is browned.
Stir in gravy, water, salt and pepper.
Arrange sliced onions and carrots on top of chops.
Pour on gravy mixture.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned raisin bread pudding
directions: Slice raisin bread into 3/4-inch pieces.
Place in shallow buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Set aside.
Heat milk with butter until hot and butter is melted (do not allow mixture to boil). Beat eggs with sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add hot milk mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour over bread.
Allow to stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon sugar.
Set baking dish in pan with hot water to half the depth of dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 50 minutes or until custard is set. Serve warm or cold.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in a quart microwave dish. Microwave on High for 4 1/4 minutes; stir and microwave on High for
another
4 1/4 minutes.
Add nuts; stir well and microwave 2 1/2 minutes.
It should be a light brown.
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda and when well mixed and foamy, spread on large pan sprayed with Pam.
Keep working with it to get it as thin as possible.
Makes 1 pound.

title: nacho chicken casserole
directions: Spray dish with Pam.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Layer chips. broth, onion, green pepper and soup and Ro-Tel mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 10 more minutes.
Set 5 minutes before serving.

title: poached salmon
directions: Heat deep fry pan.
Put salmon in middle.
Pour wine and lemon over the top.
Cut butter into thin pats and place on top of steaks.
Place lid on pan and cook 10 to 12 minutes for each inch of thickness.
Lift steaks occasionally to make sure they don't stick.
Fish is done when you can pull center bone away with no problem.
Yields 2 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel apples, core and slice into thick slices.	Combine flour, sugar
and
cinnamon.
Spread
half
this mixture over bottom
of unbaked
crust.
Add apples and sprinkle remaining sugar
mixture over
them.
Dot
margarine over pie.
Add top crust and seal edges.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in preheated oven at 425°.
Can substitute peaches or blueberries for apples.

title: sweet & sour fish
directions: Prepare sweet & sour sauce and set aside.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix and cook for several hours.
Serve over egg noodles, bow ties or rice.

title: original schimmel cheesecake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover the bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Reserve extra crumbs for topping. Refrigerate.

title: beef taco casserole
directions: Cook meat and spices until done.
Add tomato sauce and beans. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with corn chips.
Add meat mixture.
Cover top with cheese and more chips, if desired.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
When serving, add shredded lettuce and chopped onions, if desired.

title: dependable divinity
directions: Mix water and sugar in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Place Marshmallow Creme in bowl; pour hot syrup into Creme.
Beat until the mixture loses its gloss.
Add nuts, vanilla and salt.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: apple cheese bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Combine melted butter, beaten egg and milk. Set aside.

title: limeade
directions: In pitcher, add warm water. Stir in sugar until dissolved. Add lime juice and stir. Pour over ice and serve.

title: homemade dumplings
directions: Melt margarine in boiling water.
Add flour and salt.
Mix to make a soft dough.
Mixture will be quite warm.
Divide into 2 or 3 portions.
Roll out on lightly floured board to a thickness of 1/4 inch or less.
Cut into squares.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Place in airtight freezer bags.
Cook in boiling broth. Makes delicious chicken and dumplings.

title: oatmeal-molasses cookies
directions: Makes big-big batch.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, molasses, oatmeal, spices and half the flour.
Mix in a dishpan and add rest of flour.
Roll in balls, flatten with fork. Bake 7 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cheese cake
directions: Pour boiling water over jello; let cool.
Add to sugar and cheese mixture.
Chill the milk and whip.
Add to jello and cheese mixture.
Pour into graham cracker lined dish.
Sprinkle with graham crackers and sugar and chill.
Can use fruit filling.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter three minutes or until soft. Stir in flour, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook for two minutes, stirring constantly, until vegetables are coated evenly and mixture is bubbly.
Stir in broth, carrots and potatoes. Bring to boil.
Lower heat.
Cover and allow to simmer for 25 minutes or until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat until almost boiling (do not boil).
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add salt and pepper.
Makes ten servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise together until fluffy.
Fold in other ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on crackers.

title: cookie cake
directions: Slice one roll of cookie dough and place on ungreased cookie sheet (13 x 9-inch).
Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar until creamy and pour into pan.
Slice second roll of cookies and put on top of creamy mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown lightly in fat with the onion.
Add tomato juice, water and sugar.
Simmer until tender.
Ten minutes before serving, add mushrooms and sour cream. Serves 4.

title: steak soup
directions: Melt butter in pot.
Brown meat and pour off excess grease. Add flour to butter and make a roux.
Add water.
Stir with wire whip until a paste appears.
Add celery, onion and mixed vegetables and bring to a boil.
When vegetables are 1/2 finished, add remaining spices and fill pot with water and bring to a second boil.
When it boils, reduce heat and keep at a low temperature until it thickens.

title: ouida's hot corn
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine.
Cook celery, pepper and onions until tender.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add tomatoes and drained corn.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian haystacks
directions: Boil 4 cups of water and meat until done.
Debone.
Add soup to stock to make gravy.
Cook rice; drain.
Shred cheese; chop onion, mushrooms, tomatoes and green pepper.
Place each in separate bowls and serve smorgasbord.

title: magic coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on low speed for 1 minute.
Pour mixture into a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
This pie makes its own crust.
Just before placing in oven, sprinkle a small amount of the coconut over top.
Be sure to save a small amount from the cup.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in gumdrops (don't use licorice).
Add oatmeal and coconut and/or walnuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: apple crisp 1
directions: Sift together 1/2 cup sugar, flour, salt and baking powder. Add cooking oil and beaten egg.
Pare and slice apples.
Place in bottom of a shallow baking dish.
Add other 1/2 cup sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Cover with the flour mixture. Any other fruit may be used.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Prepare pie shell and bake.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over strawberries and let set for about 1 hour.
Combine sugar and cornstarch and then add water.
Cook until desired thickness. Remove from heat and add strawberry jello; mix well.
Pour this over strawberries which have been placed in baked pie shell. Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate and mix until blended.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition until batter is smooth.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper
garlic in butter.
Add rice & brown lightly, add tomatoes, broth, bay leaves, dash tabasco. Stir well and add 1 cup water.
Cook slowly, covered for about 30 to 40 mins.
Leave a little juicey.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix well.
Store in jar.
Use 1/3 cup of mix in cup.
Pour boiling water over.
Stir and serve.

title: rosemary chicken and vegetables(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Chop the carrots and steam for 10 to 12 minutes.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish twice or three times with vegetable spray.
Cut the butter into small chunks and distribute evenly over dish.
Spread the minced garlic evenly around bottom of dish and place in oven for 3 to 5 minutes (until the smell of the cooking garlic is strong).
Remove dish and put the chicken breasts on bottom.
Add the sliced zucchini, red bell pepper and banana peppers (cut into strips), steamed carrots and onion (cut in half circle shapes).
Sprinkle the rosemary over entire dish, making sure some comes in contact with the chicken breasts (use more rosemary if necessary).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover dish with tinfoil and return to oven for 40 minutes.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand one hour.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Spread carrots (already cooked) in shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish with minced parsley.

title: americana chuck pot roast
directions: Sprinkle
meat	with
salt.
Brown meat in hot oil.
In pot, add
1/2 cup water and bay leaf; simmer for 1 1/2 hours, or
until meat is tender.
Drain fat.
Add vegetables and rest of water to roast.
Pour on tomato sauce; cook 1 more hour.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Cook pumpkin and put in blender until creamy with mixer.
Add flour, sugar and beaten egg yolks to pumpkin.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Blend with mixer.
Add to pumpkin.
Add milk last. Bake at 450°
for 15 minutes.
Turn oven back to 350°.
Bake for 1/2 hour.

title: shrimp and yellow rice
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine onion and 1 tablespoon of water; cover and microwave for 12 minutes on High.
Add water, rice, both peppers, bouillon and spices.
Mix. Cover and cook on High for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 50%; cook 40 to 50 minutes. Add shrimp and tomato; mix.
Cover and cook on Medium for 5 to 8 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl; mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Shred
cabbage
and vegetables;
set aside.
Heat vinegar, 1/3 cup
sugar and oil to boiling and pour over cabbage. Mix other ingredients in and mix.
Let stand overnight.
Will keep in the refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Mix sugar and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil to dissolve sugar.
Add raw peanuts and boil over medium heat until sugar crystallizes and no syrup is left (15 to 20 minutes).
Stir while boiling to evenly coat peanuts.
Spread nuts on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes so that nuts will be evenly roasted. Remove from oven and cool.

title: toffee bars(quick and easy)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, butter, egg yolk and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt.
Press evenly into greased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake until very light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Crust will be soft.
Remove from oven; immediately place separated pieces of chocolate candy on crust.
Let stand until soft, then spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into bars, about 2 x 1 1/2-inches, while warm.
Yield: 32 cookies.

title: chicken barbecue(diet)
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Put in frying pan. Mix Coke, catsup and mustard and pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mile high cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter, mixing well.
Press into bottom and up sides of a buttered 8-inch spring-form pan. Set aside.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and crushed walnuts.
Spread in bottom of lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: molded asparagus salad
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Remove from heat and add gelatin. Stir until dissolved.
Add cheese and mix until melted.
Add water and mayonnaise. Heat until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into mold and chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: micro fudge
directions: Heat oleo in microwave for 1 minute.
Take out and mix in all other ingredients.
Put back in microwave for 1 minute.
Take out; stir with wire whip until mixed well.
Put in greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Put in fridge for a few minutes, then cut.

title: deluxe peanut butter cookies(yields 36 to 40)
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and the two sugars together.
Add eggs; add flour, soda and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with a sugared fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: jazzy hot dogs
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Slit hot dogs down the center lengthwise.
Place slit side down in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Pour mixture over.
Bake uncovered for 35 minutes.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add extracts and beat again.
Add 1/2 flour and 1/2 of eggs.
Beat, then add rest of eggs, flour and buttermilk, beating after each addition.
Bake in 3 or 4 large pans for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix 1/4 cup cherry juice with cream cheese. Whip Dream Whip.
Mix with cream cheese mixture.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.

title: magic-quick chocolate frosting
directions: Cook
milk,
chocolate	and
salt
over rapidly boiling water until thick, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add water gradually.	Cool.
Add
vanilla.
Spread
on cold cake. Will frost
tops
of 2 (9-inch) layers, top and sides of loaf cake or 24 cupcakes.

title: punch
directions: Mix together in large punch bowl.

title: diet pineapple muffins
directions: With pastry cutter or two knives cut dry ingredients and margarine together until flour mixture is the size of peas.
In another small bowl beat egg.
Add beaten egg to dry ingredients, mix gently with spoon.
Add pineapple last and mix until blended. Spray muffin tin with Pam.
Divide dough into 6 muffin tins and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandmom strouse's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to box directions.
Rinse with cool water.
Add shrimp and liquid from can.
Slice hard-boiled eggs and add to macaroni.
Dice celery and wedge tomatoes.
Add to mixture.
Add mayonnaise by tablespoon until macaroni mixture is well coated.

title: spicy apple wedges
directions: Fill a 10-inch pie pan with apple slices. In a medium bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and spices.
Mix well.
Cover apples with mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: shrimp newberg
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour.
Blend.
Add cream.
When sauce thickens, add catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Add shrimp.
Heat well.
Immediately before serving, add wine.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well and blend in milk. Combine dry ingredients; add to butter mixture.
Spread half of batter in greased 8-inch round container; cover with 3/4 can pie filling.
Spread with remaining batter; top with remaining filling.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with plain or whipped heavy cream or with vanilla ice cream.

title: cal's sweet sour spareribs
directions: Mix ingredients in deep pot and cook until meat is tender, first medium-high until it boils and then simmer.
Takes about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Cook and stir the first 4 ingredients until thick; let cool. Fold in oranges and Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: In a square 9 x 9-inch baking dish, dump the drained pineapple, the pie filling and then the cake mix on top.
Chip the butter to cover the top and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and flour; stir until smooth.
Stir in broth; cook, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Add all other ingredients, except potato chips.
Arrange a layer of crushed chips in chicken mixture.
Top with remaining chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes (until it bubbles and chips are browned).

title: poor man's coconut brownies
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and cook over low heat for about a minute, stirring well to dissolve sugar.
Add butter. Keep heating to melt.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to harden.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach under hot water; wring out.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add to spinach.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Place in loaf of bread.

title: nana's ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges real good.
Add grapes (lots), kids love them.
Then add 1/2 bag of mini marshmallows; stir in sour cream (1/2 to 3/4 of a 16 ounce container).
Chill.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Place chicken breasts, skin side up, in baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients, including mushroom liquid.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: vetkoek
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Beat the egg and mix with the dry ingredients.
Blend with water or milk to make a thin batter.
Heat enough oil in frying pan to cover the base of the pan.
Drop the batter into the hot oil by the spoonful and fry until golden brown on both sides.
Serve hot with butter, honey, syrup or cheese.

title: mini pizza
directions: Brown and crumble the sausage, along with the onion and bell pepper.
Drain meat and add cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted, then put mixture on bread.

title: fruit salad(yum, yum)
directions: Mix Cool Whip, jello and cottage cheese. Drain fruit and mix in. Chill.

title: chive dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 1/2 to 1 hour before using.

title: holly candy
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in saucepan.
Pour in remaining ingredients.
Spoon
out on wax paper.
Place 2 or 3 cinnamon red hots in center to give holly/berry look.

title: ladyfingers dessert
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
In another bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add to Dream Whip and mix.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with one layer of ladyfingers.
Spread half of the cream cheese mixture on top.
Repeat with another layer of ladyfingers and the rest of the cream cheese mixture. Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: split pea soup
directions: Wash split peas.
Add to water, then add all of the ingredients.
In crock-pot, cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
On stove top, cook 2 hours or until peas are mushy.
Use Braun hand blender to blend all ingredients together until creamy and smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour well, then add other ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked 9-inch deep dish shell.
Top with egg whites.

title: "philly" pound cake
directions: Thoroughly blend margarine, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Gradually add flour (sifted with baking powder).
Pour into waxed paper lined 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Let stand for 5 minutes; turn out of pan to cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook, drain, mash and season eggplant.
Blend together undiluted mushroom soup, mayonnaise, beaten egg and chopped onion. Mix with eggplant.
Put in buttered casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: outrageous brownies
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate and butter.
Beat sugar, eggs, vanilla and baking powder until fluffy.
Pour chocolate into egg and sugar mixture; beat until blended.
Add chocolate chips, then flour.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch pan lined with aluminum foil and sprayed with light cooking spray.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: pistachio fluff
directions: Mix together pineapple and pudding.
After this is thick mix in fruit cocktail and Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Add any or all optional ingredients.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Bake at 350° in a greased Bundt pan for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato buns
directions: Bake or broil sweet potatoes until tender.
Cool.
Remove potato from skins and mash.
(You should have 1 cup.)
In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Stir in mashed sweet potatoes, oil, brown sugar, salt and 2 cups flour.
Turn dough out onto floured board.
Knead about 8 minutes, incorporating additional flour, until dough is smooth and elastic.
Coat large bowl with oil.
Place dough in bowl, turning to coat all sides with oil. Cover, let rise until almost doubled, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down.
Divide into 12 balls.
Knead and tuck ends under each one until top is smooth.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Cover.
Let buns rise until almost doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to racks to cool.
Makes 12 buns.

title: chow mein candy
directions: Melt chips together in double boiler.
Then mix nuts and noodles with the chips.
Let cool.
Drop on wax paper by the teaspoon.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all powder ingredients in a large mixing bowl, then add liquid ingredients.
Blend well.
Use 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Leave cool.

title: rhubarb pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, yolks and oil together.
Add rhubarb, water, vanilla and cinnamon; beat well.
Add nuts and flour; mix thoroughly.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: baked tomatoes, florida style
directions: Wash and cut ripe tomatoes in half.
Lightly brush outer skin with oil.
Place, cut side up, in a baking dish.
Sprinkle cut side with salt and set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put Doritos in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chips.
Spread grated cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Combine dry ingredients together.
Stir until well mixed.
Add milk, a little at a time.
Place on stove; stir continuously until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Combine pineapple with juice and baking soda.
Mix well.
Set aside.

title: berries in the snow
directions: Tear up an angel food cake into small pieces and put into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Over this pour Dream Whip mixed with softened cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Top with fresh strawberries mixed with strawberry glaze.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in sheet pan.
Cover with marshmallows and bake until brown.
Let cool and frost.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Beat potatoes, margarine, sugar, eggs, milk, orange juice and rind with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and chill.
Serve cold.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, melt butter.
Add sugar and milk; stir well.
Microwave about 3 or 4 minutes, stirring once or twice, then cook 5 full minutes, stirring several times.
Add chips and marshmallows until melted.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour Bundt pan. Put all dry ingredients together and stir. Add liquid ingredients (eggs, oil and vanilla). Fold in pecans and pears. Place in Bundt pan and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on your stove.

title: cheese balls
directions: Allow cheeses to come to room temperature.
Mix all together in large bowl.
Separate into 2 equal size balls and roll around in your hand until round.
Roll in parsley flakes or chopped nuts. Wrap in cellophane and refrigerate.

title: zucchini salad
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over thinly sliced zucchini.
Let set at least 1 hour before serving.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Use a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir peanuts, sugar and syrup; cook for 8 minutes on High, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; cook 1 minute on High.
Add baking soda quickly; stir until foamy.
Pour into greased pizza pan.
Cool 30 minutes.
Lift out and break up with a spoon.
This is much better than Sophie Mae.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and bake in 8-inch pans at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Cook pumpkin for about 10 minutes, then drain for 30 minutes. Put 4 cups of pumpkin in oven and reheat.

title: chocolate fudge ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 5-quart freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Disregard all instructions on packages. Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar or frost with your choice of frosting.

title: 14 day sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers whole for 14 days.
Use 2 cups salt for 1 gallon water.
Keep pushed under water.
Slice up and put in alum water overnight.
Use 3 tablespoons alum per 1 gallon of water. Rinse very well.
Pour apple cider vinegar over these and soak 6 hours.
Drain, but do not rinse.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Hollow out pumpernickel or rye bread.
Cut into cubes.
Fill cavity with dip and enjoy.

title: ground beef, egg and potato skillet
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onions and potatoes; cook for 5 minutes, stirring often until onions are tender.
Beat eggs with salt and stir into meat mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until eggs are almost set.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and cook over low heat for 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve at once.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Scald milk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk which has been cooled to lukewarm. Add sugar, shortening and salt.
Add flour and soda which have been sifted together.
Mix well and let stand in bowl 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased pan and allow to rise 30 minutes. Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Brush with butter.
Bake in hot oven 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 24 biscuits.

title: 3 color pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Rinse with cold water. Add rest of ingredients as you wish and garnish with bacon bits. Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.
Enjoy!

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine gelatine and water; set aside.
Cook vinegar and sugar until sugar dissolves; cool.
Beat in remaining ingredients with hand mixer.
Will keep a week or so.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out very thin; cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 300° for about 20 minutes.

title: easy does it lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef in medium saucepan.
Stir in tomato
sauce,
Italian
seasoning,
oregano,
salt
and
onion flakes; set
aside.
Mix
cottage
cheese
and
yogurt.
Spread about 1 cup tomato
mixture
in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan. Combine Parmesan cheese and garlic and chives seasoning.
Layer a third
each
of
noodles, cottage cheese mixture, Mozzarella, remaining tomato
mixture
and Parmesan mixture;
repeat twice. Pour in water around sides of pan.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 8 to 10 minutes
longer
or
until
noodles are tender and top is golden.
Let
stand
minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Spread 1 1/3 cups stuffing into greased, 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds, turkey and green beans.
Combine soup and milk and pour over top.
Moisten remaining dressing with hot water and butter and spread over top.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 3 minutes, then quickly add the remaining ingredients and stir.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and let cool.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: italian sausage brunch(breakfast food)
directions: Place 6 slices of bread in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook sausage and next 3 ingredients in a large skillet over medium heat until sausage is browned; drain well.
Spoon half of sausage mixture over bread; sprinkle half of cheese over sausage.
Layer remaining 6 slices of bread, sausage mixture and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix flour and dry ingredients; add to butter, sugar, eggs and sour cream.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, half of batter. Over that pour fruit pie filling.
Pour on rest of the batter.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Slice thin 1 head cauliflower.
Slice radishes.
Mix together. This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until done in middle.
Serve with warm flour tortillas.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Pour into 9-inch uncooked shell and place in preheated oven at 400°, then reset at 350° and cook 40 minutes until filling is set in center.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken; debone and skin.
Cut into pieces.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix soup, Miracle Whip, curry powder and lemon juice and save.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish broccoli first, chicken second, sauce third, sprinkle cheese on top fourth and sprinkle bread crumbs on top fifth.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow dish or zip-top plastic bag; add salad dressing. Cover or seal; refrigerate 1 hour. Remove chicken from marinade, discarding marinade. Dredge chicken in cornflakes; place on a rack in a broiler pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes or until tender. Yield 4 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook onion in melted oleo; add to mixture of remaining ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese cake squares
directions: Mix butter and crumbs and line a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Beat the sugar, eggs and vanilla together until smooth and creamy (at least 5 minutes).
Pour over crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°. Cool slightly.
Top with following mixture.

title: family sized broccoli casserole(yields 10 servings)
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Combine remaining ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Mix well. Stir into broccoli.
Pour into buttered dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Place frozen rolls in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle dry mix over rolls.
Melt butter and drizzle over top.
Let stand overnight.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend cheeses in mixing bowl.
Add garlic powder and peppers. Enjoy!

title: squash pie
directions: Mix spices, flour, salt and sugar well.
Add squash and mix. Add slightly beaten eggs.
Scald milk and add to mixture.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 450° about 15 minutes until crust is set, then reduce heat to 300° and bake about 45 minutes or until done.

title: pignoli cookies
directions: Mix eggs and sugar together.
Add almond paste and mix well. Roll into balls and roll into pignoli.
Dip hands in water while rolling.
Grease cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt into a large mixing bowl; stir in corn meal.
Add eggs, milk, butter, green pepper, onion and pimentos.
Beat vigorously with electric mixer or hand rotary beater until all ingredients are well mixed, about 1 minute.
Turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Delicious served with creamed chicken.

title: kailey's soup(fast and easy)
directions: Brown onion and hamburger; drain off excess fat.
In stew pan add corn, tomatoes, tomato sauce, carrots and water; add onion and hamburger.
Cook macaroni separately, rinse and drain well.
Add to soup.
Then sprinkle salt, pepper, garlic salt, and oregano (pinch) to taste to soup.
Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in salted water for 10 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Heat oven to 425°.
Combine carrots, onion salt, green pepper, and pepper.
Alternate layers of carrots and crumbs in greased baking dish.
Then pour on butter and top with cheese and bake 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: lola's egg custard
directions: Mix well.
Pour in an oiled iron skillet.
Cook at 300° for 45 minutes or until as brown as you like.

title: barbecue sauce(good with ribs)
directions: Cook until thick. Pour over ribs and bake.

title: mom's hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic until tender.
Drain off grease.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder and paprika.
Cover with water and simmer 2-3 hours.
Add water to keep meat covered while cooking.
Cool.
Add ketchup and Worcestershire sauce. Makes a lot of chili, so freeze in small containers for future use.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 8-inch, two-crust pie as directed on package.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Put half of the green peppers and half of the vinegar into blender container; cover and process at the liquify setting until peppers are liquified.
Pour into a saucepan.
Repeat with remaining peppers and vinegar.
Add sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil and add pectin.
Boil until it thickens when dropped from a spoon about 20 minutes.
Add a few drops of green food coloring. Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: sweet-and-sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 5 tablespoons juice. Set pineapple aside. Combine 2 tablespoons pineapple juice, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 2 tablespoons cornstarch, stirring until smooth. Add pork. Cover and chill 15 minutes. Stir-fry garlic, onion and bell pepper in 2 tablespoons hot oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat 2 minutes or until crisp-tender. Remove from skillet. Drain pork, discarding marinade. Stir-fry pork in remaining 2 tablespoons oil 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Pour off excess oil. Stir in cooked vegetables. Combine remaining 3 tablespoons pineapple juice, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 3 tablespoons cornstarch, sugar and remaining 3 ingredients, stirring until smooth. Add to pork mixture, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil. Add pineapple chunks. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Serve over hot cooked rice. Makes 8 servings.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Add sugar to beaten (stiff) egg white; beat until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Blend.
Add pecans and stir until nuts are well coated. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to directions. Add broccoli and carrots for the last 4 minutes of cooking time to make mixture. Drain. In a skillet, heat margarine. Add chicken and fry until browned, stirring often. Add soup, milk, cheese and fettuccine mixture and cook through, stirring often. Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecued lima beans
directions: Wash and soak beans in cold water overnight; rinse and drain. Add 4 cups water and chopped onion.
Bring to a boil and cover; reduce heat and simmer until just tender (about 45 to 60 minutes). Combine other ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Stir into beans.
Pour into large casserole or small roaster and bake, uncovered, in 250° to 300° oven for several hours.

title: russian tea
directions: Slice oranges and lemons thin.
Cover with sugar and let stand one hour or more.
Cover tea with the boiling water.
Strain over fruit, cloves and cinnamon.
Let simmer two hours.
Add pineapple juice.
Serve hot.
Serves 35.

title: south of the border bundles
directions: Wrap tortillas tightly in foil.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cut process cheese spread in 6 sticks.
In a mixing bowl, stir together beans, 1/2 cup green onions, chili peppers and chili powder

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together and set aside.
Combine oil and sugar; mix well and add one at a time to your eggs.
Beat well after each addition.
Gradually add your dry ingredients and your grated carrots.
Bake in 350° oven until done (will make 3 layers).

title: old time beef stew
directions: Heat fat in Dutch oven. Add beef and brown on all sides. Brown about 20 minutes. Add onion and garlic (put garlic on toothpick so you can retrieve it).
Add the boiling water, salt, lemon juice, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, paprika, bay leaf and allspice. Cook, covered, and simmer about 2 hours. Stir often.
When meat is almost done, add vegetables. Simmer 30 minutes. Discard bay leaf.
Pour 1/2 cup cold water into shaker. Add 1/4 cup flour.
Mix well.
Add to stew.
Cook and stir until gravy thickens.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: mandarin meatloaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except sweet & sour sauce; mix well. Shape ground beef into loaf; press into 9 x 5 - inch loaf pan. Pour sweet & sour sauce over loaf; return to oven. Continue baking 20 minutes. Garnish, if desired. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: squash souffle(lo-fat)
directions: Steam squash until very tender (about 10 minutes).
Transfer to food processor. Add egg substitute, cinnamon and nutmeg. Puree, then transfer to a large bowl.

title: broccoli and cheddar soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in the crock. Stir well. Cover and cook on low 8 hours or high 4 hours. Stir midway or about 1 hour before serving. Makes about 4 1/2 quarts.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, then mash while still hot.
Cook onion in butter until tender and lightly browned.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth. Slowly stir in water.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and add milk.
Heat until hot but not boiling.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in a 400° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until soft. Cut in half and scoop out flesh.
Fry bacon for 5 minutes; add onion and cook another 5 minutes.
Mash the potatoes and add bacon, onion, mustard, egg, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well. Fill the potato skins with mixture and sprinkle with paprika. Serves 4 to 8.

title: spiked punch
directions: Mix juices together.
Pour into punch bowl.
Now add the 7-up and Southern Comfort and mix with juices.

title: elegant italian flavored chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Coat chicken breasts; set aside.
Saute onion in butter; blend in flour.
Stir in milk all at once; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook 1 minute more.
Stir in spinach and ham.
Place spinach mixture in pan.
Place chicken breasts on top.

title: tuna apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except lettuce in a bowl.
Serve on bed of lettuce or use in sandwiches.

title: "garides" - shrimp tourkolimano
directions: In a skillet, heat oil; add shrimp and cook for about 1 minute until shrimp curl and turn pink.
Add scallions, tomatoes and mushrooms and stir until well mixed with shrimp.
Add crumbled cheese and mix well; cook for about 1 1/2 minutes.
Add wine and simmer for 1 more minute.
Remove from heat.
Place in a heated dish and serve immediately over boiled rice.
Serves 4.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare oven to 425°.
Combine filling ingredients.
Mix well and pour into shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Wrap brisket in foil.
Cover with the first 8 ingredients that have been mixed together.
Marinate overnight.
Cook 6 hours in a 250° oven.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pie shell.
Simmer until thick.
Pour into pie shell; cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter in a large skillet.
Add ground beef; brown.
Spoon off fat, add salt and pepper.
Stir in 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
May cook in same skillet, or pour in casserole dish.
Top with layer of Tater Tots.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: bean soup(crock-pot cooking)
directions: Soak beans for 8 hours (overnight).
Chop (coarse) green pepper, celery and onion.
Add these and broken up tomatoes to drained beans.
Add precooked beef, ham and seasoning; simmer until the beans are done (to taste).

title: frozen peach cream pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk, peaches, ReaLemon and extract.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crusts.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm. Return leftovers to freezer.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Take the warm water and yeast, mix and add sugar, instant potatoes and corn oil.
Then add bread flour and mix.
Put out on floured board and knead.
Pinch off in balls the size of golf balls.
Put in pan and let rise 6 to 8 hours.
Spray pan and top of biscuits and put wax paper on top to let rise.
Once they have doubled in size, bake at 350° until brown.

title: quick corned beef hash
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until tender.
Take the corned beef and cut into chunks; add to potatoes.
Cook until beef is hot.
Do not stir, beef will come apart.

title: never fail chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Cook over medium heat.
When mixture comes to a boil, boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla; beat to spreading consistency.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Cut cakes into small pieces.
Mix pudding with milk and sour cream.
Layer Ding Dongs, pudding, Cool Whip.
Makes 2 layers.

title: mom's holiday mince-nut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a large bowl. In a medium bowl, combine eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Stir in mincemeat and nuts.
Pour egg mixture into dry ingredients; stir only enough to moisten flour.
Spoon batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan to rack; cool completely.
If desired, sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: spiced peach butter
directions: In a large skillet, cook peaches in water until tender. Press through a sieve or process in a food processor. Measure 8 cups pulp. Return to kettle. Add sugar, ginger and nutmeg. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 30 minutes. Immediately ladle into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps. Process for 10 minutes in a boiling water bath. Yield: 4 pints.

title: fastest cake in the west
directions: Mix all ingredients in an ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serve from pan. Top with Cool Whip or serve warm with ice cream if desired.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Mix at low speed until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and pineapple.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes on rack.
Let cool.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: finnish cardamon bread tree
directions: In a large bowl combine 1 2/2 c. flour and the yeast.
In a saucepan heat the milk, sugar, butter, cardamon and salt just until warm (120-130°), stirring constantly.
Add to the flour mixture, along with the eggs.
Beat with an electric mixer on low, scraping sides constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high.
Stir in as much remaining flour as you can mix in with a spoon.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix flour, 1 teaspoon sugar and salt.
Add egg yolk mixture. Divide in half.
Roll 1/2 out and put in bottom of jelly roll pan. Sprinkle cornflakes over.
Add apples, sliced and sugar.
Cover with remaining dough, rolled out.
Brush with egg white.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Frost with Powdered Sugar Frosting.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup milk with cream cheese and rest of milk and pudding mix.
Mix well.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Top with fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix vegetable oil and dressing mix.
Stir in crackers until oil mixture is absorbed.

title: elegant party cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package.
Pour batter onto floured cookie sheet with sides.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Set aside. Cool 5 minutes.
Dissolve pudding with milk and set aside.
Cream the cheese.
Add whipped topping and beat.
Add pudding and beat again.
Mixture should be the consistency of whipped cream. Spread mixture over cooled cake.
Drain pineapple well and spread over pudding mixture, then sprinkle with coconut and crushed walnuts.
Put cherry in each square (30 squares).

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake and cook pie shell.
Wash berries; remove hulls.
Crush 1 cup of berries and cook with the 1 cup water for 2 minutes. Drain well with sieve; reserve juice.
Add water if needed to make 1 1/4 cups juice.
Discard cooked berries.
In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; stir in berry juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and clear.
Spread a small amount of the glaze mixture (about 1/4 cup) on bottom and sides of pie shell.
Fill pie shell with remaining berries, stem end down. Spoon glaze on all berries.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip sandwich cookies
directions: Prepare cookies and bake as directed on cookie mix.

title: baked chop suey casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute chopped celery and onion in butter or margarine.
In separate skillet, brown hamburger.
In separate saucepan, cook rice. After all above items cook, add to a baking dish and stir with cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups. Do not add water to soups.
Stir in soy sauce. Once completely stirred and smoothed over in baking dish, add cracker or bread crumbs by spreading on top.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: monkey face cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by spoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Add raisins to make monkey faces.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Toss 1/2 cup sugar, 1 cup pecans, 20 rolled Ritz Crackers and 3/4 tsp. vanilla.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients in baking dish.
Top with more catsup.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel eggplant.
Cut crosswise about 1/2-inch thick.
Place slices onto nonstick baking sheet.
Brush with 1/8 cup oil.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix butter, sugar, milk and vanilla thoroughly.
Add coconut and nuts.
Make into small balls and chill.
Melt together chocolate chips and wax.
Stir until well blended.
Dip each ball into mixture and place on waxed paper to cool.
Keep dip hot and use sparingly or you will not have enough to cover all the balls.

title: gingerbread men
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Stir in eggs and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Knead with hands until a smooth ball of dough forms.
Roll out on a heavily floured surface.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutter or by hand.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, decorate with white frosting.
Makes approximately 24 cookies, 4 inches high.

title: easy chocolate dessert hershey bar pie
directions: Melt marshmallows into milk in double boiler.
Break into that the Hershey bars.
Melt and stir.
Cool completely, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and chill until ready to serve.

title: lemon-sugar glaze for hot cake
directions: Mix well and slowly pour over cake while hot.
It sinks in and gives a good flavor to the cake.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine and beat sugar, mustard, salt and wine vinegar.
Add salad oil slowly, continuing beating.
Last, add poppy seed and stir.
Chill before serving.
Makes 3 cups.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. In an 11 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, combine spaghetti with sauce, pepperoni, mushrooms and onion. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cover chicken with water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Remove chicken and reserve broth.
Debone chicken and shred; set aside.
Saute celery and onion in butter until soft.
Add flour.
Cook and stir until golden brown.
Add reserved broth, salt and black pepper.
Bring to a boil; add noodles.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Stir in half and half.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix half batter at a time and transfer to a large container.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; beat into egg mixture.
Add dates and nuts.
Bake in a lightly greased 7 x 11-inch pan in slow oven for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut while still hot.
Store loosely covered.
Keeps for days.

title: apricot pie
directions: Quarter apricots and boil with water.
Cook 10 minutes over medium heat.
Add sugar and cook 5 minutes more.
Drain, reserving 3/4 cup juice.
Set apricots aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice; set pineapple aside.
Mix juices with cornstarch and dash of salt.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat, until mixture thickens.
Mix drained apricots and pineapple.
Mix with thickened juices.
Pour into unbaked bottom crust.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and pierce.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes until done.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown hamburger and onion; pour off excess grease.

title: scrumptious chocolate cake
directions: Cream the regular sugar and cream cheese in a mixing bowl. Gradually add the powdered sugar. Fold in the Cool Whip and three of the Hershey bars, grated. Ice the inside layers of the three cakes plus the top.
Sprinkle the fourth Hershey candy bar on top of the cake. Must be refrigerated.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in apples.
Mix dry ingredients and add to batter.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased loaf cake pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain and halve artichoke hearts.
Cook beans in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Toss with other ingredients.
Chill and serve on bibb lettuce.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Boil sugar and pineapple for 5 minutes.
Add jello and cheese to sugar mixture and mix.
Stir until jello and cheese dissolve. Cool mix.
Beat can of evaporated milk until fluffy (will get thick).
Fold into pineapple mix.

title: oatmeal-coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter; add brown sugar and sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg, vanilla and milk; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, powder and salt.
Add and beat in.
Add oatmeal and coconut. Stir in.
Drop cookies 2 inches apart on a well-greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook chocolate, sugar and milk for 8 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Test in cold water.
Add vanilla and butter; beat until begins to thicken.

title: apple cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Unroll crescent rolls and separate into 8 triangles.
Cut each in half lengthwise to make 16 triangles. Place an apple slice at wide end of each triangle and roll up. Arrange in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle with butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over rolls.
Pour orange juice into pan, but not over rolls.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: It will take about 2 bunches of rhubarb to make 1 1/2 to 2 cups of small pieces.
Put these into a strainer and pour boiling water over them; drain.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with the pastry; pour in the blanched rhubarb.
Mix together the sugar, flour, eggs and salt; pour this over the rhubarb.
Dot with the butter cut in small pieces.
Cover with the lattice top of the pastry or a plain top, well pierced.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool, but do not chill.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, banana and vanilla. Stir together dry ingredients and add with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes. Makes 1 loaf.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Drain sauerkraut and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place tomatoes evenly on top.
Dot with dressing and margarine.
Spread corned beef.
Evenly cut and layer on Swiss cheese.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll soft dough into small balls.
Flatten on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 minutes at 400°.

title: apple pie's brother
directions: Slice the apples and put into a buttered baking dish.
To make the crumbs, sift together the salt, baking powder, flour and sugar.
Add the egg to the flour mixture and stir with a fork. Put these crumbs over the apples.
Pour the melted shortening over the crumbs.
Dust with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until the apples are done.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream or alone.
This recipe has been in my family for 5 generations!

title: cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, sift together sugar and flour.
Stir in marshmallows; set aside.
In saucepan, combine butter, oil, cocoa and Coca-Cola; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; remove from heat and pour mixture over dry ingredients; blend well.
Add buttermilk, baking soda, eggs and vanilla, mixing well after each addition.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with additional butter or Pam.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; remove cake from oven and frost immediately.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Lightly beat together egg and soy sauce in pie pan or shallow bowl.
Combine contents of gravy mix envelope and sesame seed. Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture, then roll in gravy mixture until well coated.
Melt butter in large, shallow baking pan. Place chicken, side down down, in pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer, until crisp and brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chile con queso
directions: In hot butter in medium skillet, saute onion until tender.
Add tomatoes, chiles and salt, mashing tomatoes with fork.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Add cheese cubes, stirring until cheese is melted.
Stir in cream.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes.
Serve warm in bowl with corn chips and tortillas.

title: california strawberry for crepes
directions: Beat heavy cream until stiff on low speed.
Beat in sour cream along with powdered sugar and vanilla.
Chill mixture while preparing Strawberry Sauce and crepes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except pie shell. Mix well.
Pour pumpkin mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in the center of the pie comes out clean.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: low-calorie chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Boil noodles like described on package.
When noodles are cooked, drain all but an inch of water out of pan.
Drain all water from chicken and tear chicken into small pieces and add noodles.
Add cream of chicken soup and mix. Season to taste.
Contains only 10 fat grams for the whole pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/4 cup catsup with all other ingredients.
With wet hands, shape into a loaf in a 9-inch square pan.
Spread remaining 1/4 cup catsup over top.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in oven or microwave until done. Peel by choice and slice. Lay in greased baking dish. Add salt and pepper, bacon bits and then top with cheese. Bake at 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes. Before serving, add sour cream and green onions on tops.

title: dump cake
directions: Place fruit in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle coconut on top
of
fruit.
Sprinkle cake mix over coconut.
Sprinkle pecans over
cake
mix.
Dot margarine over top.
Bake at 300° until toothpick tests clean.

title: cajun cabbage(makes 10 servings.  prep time: 20 minutes.)
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef with onion; drain. Mix Ro-Tel, stewed tomatoes, garlic powder, sugar, salt and pepper.

title: potato custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes. Enjoy!

title: cherry chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Place on the unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from the heat for 6 minutes. Brush with some of the lemon juice.
Turn poultry over.
Brush with remaining lemon juice.
Broil 6 to 9 minutes or until tender and no longer pink.

title: halloween party dip
directions: In a bowl, combine pumpkin, marmalade, yogurt and spices; mix well.
Fold whipped cream into pumpkin mixture and spoon into serving dish placed on large platter.
Chill before serving. Sprinkle with nuts.
Place dippers around party dip on platter. This is great with fruit, especially apples and bananas.

title: kathie's pot pie
directions: Thaw pie crusts according to package directions.
Place one crust in bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.
Cube potatoes, beef and quarter onion.
Place in pie crust.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with second pie crust.
Vent with knife (slits).
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are tender.
Cover with foil if crust becomes brown too quickly.

title: chunky beef stew
directions: Frozen veggies may include corn, green beans or snow peas, etc.

title: spice syrup pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Using electric mixer, cream Crisco and sugar.
Add syrup.
Sift together spices, salt, baking soda and flour.
Alternate flour mixture with eggs and buttermilk to sugar mix.
Pour into lined greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake about 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: nyda's wild rice soup
directions: Cook wild rice about 35 minutes.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Sprinkle in flour and stir into mix.
Slowly add heated chicken broth.
Stir until well blended.
Season.
Add rice and chicken and mix.
Stir in half and half and sliced mushrooms. Simmer.
Serves 8 to 10.
